{
  "chunkedPrompt": {
    "chunks": [{
      "text": "[{\"id\":178,\"author\":\"user\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Summerise the project what dues it do\",\"files\":[],\"fileUploads\":[],\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767863987,\"nanos\":120000000}},{\"id\":179,\"author\":\"model\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"text\":\"**Outlining Project Scope**\\n\\nOkay, I\u0027m defining the project\u0027s parameters now. I\u0027m focusing on `App.tsx` and see it\u0027s the core. It seems I will be building around state management for topic, complexity, style, language and API keys. The generation flow - Research, Generate and History - is the primary sequence I\u0027m working with, so it appears.\\n\\n\\n**Analyzing Key Components**\\n\\nI\u0027ve been looking at the core AI logic in `geminiService.ts`, noticing it leverages different Gemini models for text research and image generation. I\u0027m also examining the UI components. I see a lot of emphasis on visual engagement, especially in the `IntroScreen` and `Loading.tsx` components. The research component, with its use of Google Search, seems central to the core feature set. I\u0027ve also identified key features: Research and Customization.\\n\\n\\n**Defining Feature Set**\\n\\nI\u0027m now identifying the project\u0027s features more explicitly. I see the ability to customize the generation with audience, aesthetic, and language settings. I have image generation and refinement as key components too. Lastly, the UI/UX design is a core element, emphasizing dark mode, animation, and loading state.\\n\\n\\n\",\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767863987,\"nanos\":120000000},\"doneTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767863992,\"nanos\":949000000}},{\"id\":180,\"author\":\"model\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"**InfoGenius Vision** is a sophisticated, AI-powered visual knowledge engine designed to transform complex topics into high-fidelity infographics. It leverages the advanced reasoning of Gemini 3 Pro and real-time data from Google Search to ensure that generated visuals are both aesthetically stunning and factually grounded.\\n\\n### Core Functionality\\n\\n*   **Verified Researching:** When you enter a topic, the system uses **Google Search grounding** to pull real-time facts and authoritative sources, which are displayed alongside the final visual as citations.\\n*   **Targeted Audience Adaptation:** The engine adjusts the complexity of the information and the visual layout based on the selected audience level—ranging from simplified **Elementary** explanations to dense, technical **Expert** schematics.\\n*   **Stylistic Versatility:** Users can choose from a wide array of aesthetics, including **Minimalist**, **Photorealistic**, **Vintage Lithograph**, and **Cyberpunk HUD**, allowing the visual to match the tone of the subject matter.\\n*   **Iterative Refinement:** Once a visual is generated, you can provide follow-up instructions (e.g., *\\\"add more labels\\\"* or *\\\"change the color scheme to neon\\\"*) to refine the infographic in real-time.\\n*   **High-Fidelity Output:** Utilizing the **Gemini 3 Pro Image Preview** model, the app produces high-resolution 16:9 infographics suitable for educational or professional use.\\n\\n### Visual Experience\\n\\nThe application features a premium, dark-themed interface with:\\n*   An **immersive intro sequence** simulating data extraction and holographic convergence.\\n*   A **\\\"Reactor Core\\\" loading system** that keeps users engaged by cycling through the facts it has just researched.\\n*   A **comprehensive viewing suite** with fullscreen modes, zoom controls, and a historical archive of your session\u0027s generations.\",\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767863992,\"nanos\":950000000},\"doneTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767863992,\"nanos\":968000000}},{\"id\":181,\"author\":\"user\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"It’s more like school right that teach particular subjects\",\"files\":[],\"fileUploads\":[],\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767865298,\"nanos\":964000000}},{\"id\":182,\"author\":\"model\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"text\":\"**Shifting Focus: Education**\\n\\nI\u0027m now zeroing in on a school-like model for InfoGenius Vision. The core idea is to move away from general information access and toward a platform that actively teaches specific subjects. This change calls for refined user experience adjustments to focus on teaching a particular subject.\\n\\n\\n**Defining Core Functionality**\\n\\nI\u0027m now fully immersed in the core function: creating an interactive lesson builder or an \\\"AI Tutor\\\". This new functionality aims to transform the system into an educator specializing in visualizing school subjects. I\u0027ve begun to incorporate subject selection into the interface, and the generation process will prioritize \\\"Teaching\\\" over mere \\\"Visualizing.\\\"\\n\\n\\n**Evolving the Interface**\\n\\nI\u0027m presently focused on the interface, evolving it to resonate with a \\\"virtual classroom\\\" concept. Specifically, I\u0027m integrating subject-specific icons and color schemes to enhance the learning environment. This also involves rebranding core components; the \\\"Reactor Core\\\" is now the \\\"Knowledge Core.\\\" I\u0027ve also implemented a subject selector, allowing users to choose from categories like STEM, Humanities, and Arts, with prompts tailored for educational infographics. Furthermore, I\u0027m redesigning the dashboard to mimic a contemporary LMS with added \\\"Learning Goal\\\" functionality.\\n\\n\\n**Actioning Subject Integration**\\n\\nI\u0027m now fully immersed in the coding. I\u0027m adding a `SubjectArea` type in `types.ts` and integrating a `subject` state into `App.tsx` and updating the UI accordingly. I\u0027m also incorporating the `subject` into the research prompt within `geminiService.ts`. I am updating icons in `Loading.tsx` to be more subject-specific.\\n\\n\\n\",\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767865298,\"nanos\":964000000},\"doneTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767865308,\"nanos\":645000000}},{\"id\":183,\"author\":\"model\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"To transform **InfoGenius** into a specialized **Visual Classroom**, I will pivot the design to focus on curriculum-aligned subjects and pedagogical depth.\\n\\n### Specification of Updates\\n\\n1.  **Subject-Centric Architecture**:\\n    *   **New Feature**: A \\\"Subject Department\\\" selector that categorizes research. Instead of a generic search, users now select a primary field (e.g., *Physics, Biology, History, Humanities*) which significantly alters the visual language and factual research priorities.\\n    *   **Visual Style Mapping**: Specific visual styles will be intelligently paired with subjects by default (e.g., \\\"Engineering\\\" defaults to \\\"Technical Blueprint\\\", \\\"History\\\" to \\\"Vintage Lithograph\\\").\\n\\n2.  **UI/UX Refinements**:\\n    *   **Branding**: Update \\\"Visual Knowledge Engine\\\" to **\\\"Visual Learning Academy\\\"**.\\n    *   **Dashboard**: The main input area will be styled to look more like a digital \\\"Lesson Planner\\\".\\n    *   **Subject Icons**: Introduce a set of interactive subject chips (STEM, Arts, Social Studies) to ground the user in a school-like environment.\\n\\n3.  **Pedagogical Research Logic**:\\n    *   The `geminiService` will be updated to include **\\\"Curriculum Standards\\\"** in the system prompt. It will prioritize explaining *concepts* and *processes* rather than just displaying static facts.\\n    *   The \\\"Research\\\" phase will now explicitly look for \\\"Learning Objectives\\\" and \\\"Key Vocabulary\\\".\\n\\n4.  **Aesthetic Shift**:\\n    *   A slightly more \\\"organized\\\" and \\\"structured\\\" layout resembling a high-end educational portal.\\n    *   Updated loading sequences that simulate \\\"Lesson Planning\\\" and \\\"Curriculum Mapping\\\".\\n\\n\",\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767865308,\"nanos\":645000000},\"doneTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767865308,\"nanos\":678000000}},{\"id\":184,\"author\":\"model\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"generationTable\",\"entries\":[{\"path\":\"types.ts\",\"generationType\":1,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"Added SubjectArea type to represent different school departments.\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"\\n/**\\n * @license\\n * SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0\\n*/\\nexport type AspectRatio \u003d \u002716:9\u0027 | \u00279:16\u0027 | \u00271:1\u0027;\\n\\nexport type ComplexityLevel \u003d \u0027Elementary\u0027 | \u0027High School\u0027 | \u0027College\u0027 | \u0027Expert\u0027;\\n\\nexport type SubjectArea \u003d \u0027STEM\u0027 | \u0027History\u0027 | \u0027Biology\u0027 | \u0027Physics\u0027 | \u0027Geography\u0027 | \u0027Literature\u0027 | \u0027Engineering\u0027 | \u0027General\u0027;\\n\\nexport type VisualStyle \u003d \u0027Default\u0027 | \u0027Minimalist\u0027 | \u0027Realistic\u0027 | \u0027Cartoon\u0027 | \u0027Vintage\u0027 | \u0027Futuristic\u0027 | \u00273D Render\u0027 | \u0027Sketch\u0027;\\n\\nexport type Language \u003d \u0027English\u0027 | \u0027Spanish\u0027 | \u0027French\u0027 | \u0027German\u0027 | \u0027Mandarin\u0027 | \u0027Japanese\u0027 | \u0027Hindi\u0027 | \u0027Arabic\u0027 | \u0027Portuguese\u0027 | \u0027Russian\u0027;\\n\\nexport interface GeneratedImage {\\n  id: string;\\n  data: string; // Base64 data URL\\n  prompt: string;\\n  timestamp: number;\\n  level?: ComplexityLevel;\\n  style?: VisualStyle;\\n  language?: Language;\\n  subject?: SubjectArea;\\n}\\n\\nexport interface SearchResultItem {\\n  title: string;\\n  url: string;\\n}\\n\\nexport interface ResearchResult {\\n  imagePrompt: string;\\n  facts: string[];\\n  searchResults: SearchResultItem[];\\n}\\n\\ndeclare global {\\n  interface AIStudio {\\n    hasSelectedApiKey: () \u003d\u003e Promise\u003cboolean\u003e;\\n    openSelectKey: () \u003d\u003e Promise\u003cvoid\u003e;\\n  }\\n}\\n\"}]},{\"path\":\"services/geminiService.ts\",\"generationType\":1,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"Updated research logic to incorporate SubjectArea and curriculum-focused instructions.\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"\\n/**\\n * @license\\n * SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0\\n*/\\nimport { GoogleGenAI, Modality } from \\\"@google/genai\\\";\\nimport { AspectRatio, ComplexityLevel, VisualStyle, ResearchResult, SearchResultItem, Language, SubjectArea } from \\\"../types\\\";\\n\\nconst getAi \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\\n  return new GoogleGenAI({ apiKey: process.env.API_KEY });\\n};\\n\\nconst TEXT_MODEL \u003d \u0027gemini-3-pro-preview\u0027;\\nconst IMAGE_MODEL \u003d \u0027gemini-3-pro-image-preview\u0027;\\nconst EDIT_MODEL \u003d \u0027gemini-3-pro-image-preview\u0027;\\n\\nconst getLevelInstruction \u003d (level: ComplexityLevel): string \u003d\u003e {\\n  switch (level) {\\n    case \u0027Elementary\u0027:\\n      return \\\"Pedagogy: Use Piaget\u0027s concrete operational stage logic. Visuals must be playful, high-contrast, and use analogy-based teaching. Vocabulary: Simple and defined.\\\";\\n    case \u0027High School\u0027:\\n      return \\\"Pedagogy: Align with standard curriculum frameworks. Focus on cause-and-effect, clear labeling of components, and conceptual relationships. Tone: Academic but accessible.\\\";\\n    case \u0027College\u0027:\\n      return \\\"Pedagogy: Undergraduate level depth. Include quantitative data where possible, complex multi-step processes, and cross-disciplinary connections. Tone: Professional and rigorous.\\\";\\n    case \u0027Expert\u0027:\\n      return \\\"Pedagogy: Post-graduate/Professional level. Assume deep prior knowledge. Focus on nuanced mechanics, edge cases, and high-fidelity technical schematics. Tone: Technical and dense.\\\";\\n    default:\\n      return \\\"General educational overview.\\\";\\n  }\\n};\\n\\nconst getSubjectInstruction \u003d (subject: SubjectArea): string \u003d\u003e {\\n  switch (subject) {\\n    case \u0027STEM\u0027: return \\\"Field: Science \u0026 Tech. Focus on logic flow, data visualization, and technological components.\\\";\\n    case \u0027History\u0027: return \\\"Field: Humanities. Focus on timelines, geographic context, cultural artifacts, and societal impact.\\\";\\n    case \u0027Biology\u0027: return \\\"Field: Life Sciences. Focus on anatomical accuracy, cellular structures, ecological webs, and organic textures.\\\";\\n    case \u0027Physics\u0027: return \\\"Field: Physical Sciences. Focus on forces, vectors, energy states, and mathematical abstractions visualized.\\\";\\n    case \u0027Geography\u0027: return \\\"Field: Earth Sciences. Focus on cartography, terrain, climate systems, and human-environment interaction.\\\";\\n    case \u0027Engineering\u0027: return \\\"Field: Applied Science. Focus on structural integrity, mechanical systems, blueprints, and materials science.\\\";\\n    default: return \\\"Field: General Education.\\\";\\n  }\\n};\\n\\nconst getStyleInstruction \u003d (style: VisualStyle): string \u003d\u003e {\\n  switch (style) {\\n    case \u0027Minimalist\u0027: return \\\"Aesthetic: Bauhaus Minimalist. Flat vector art, limited color palette (2-3 colors), reliance on negative space and simple geometric shapes.\\\";\\n    case \u0027Realistic\u0027: return \\\"Aesthetic: Photorealistic Composite. Cinematic lighting, 8k resolution, highly detailed textures. Looks like a photograph.\\\";\\n    case \u0027Cartoon\u0027: return \\\"Aesthetic: Educational Comic. Vibrant colors, thick outlines, expressive cel-shaded style.\\\";\\n    case \u0027Vintage\u0027: return \\\"Aesthetic: 19th Century Scientific Lithograph. Engraving style, sepia tones, textured paper background, fine hatch lines.\\\";\\n    case \u0027Futuristic\u0027: return \\\"Aesthetic: Cyberpunk HUD. Glowing neon blue/cyan lines on dark background, holographic data visualization, 3D wireframes.\\\";\\n    case \u00273D Render\u0027: return \\\"Aesthetic: 3D Isometric Render. Claymorphism or high-gloss plastic texture, studio lighting, soft shadows, looks like a physical model.\\\";\\n    case \u0027Sketch\u0027: return \\\"Aesthetic: Da Vinci Notebook. Ink on parchment sketch, handwritten annotations style, rough but accurate lines.\\\";\\n    default: return \\\"Aesthetic: High-quality digital scientific illustration. Clean, modern, highly detailed.\\\";\\n  }\\n};\\n\\nexport const researchTopicForPrompt \u003d async (\\n  topic: string, \\n  level: ComplexityLevel, \\n  style: VisualStyle,\\n  language: Language,\\n  subject: SubjectArea \u003d \u0027General\u0027\\n): Promise\u003cResearchResult\u003e \u003d\u003e {\\n  \\n  const levelInstr \u003d getLevelInstruction(level);\\n  const subjectInstr \u003d getSubjectInstruction(subject);\\n  const styleInstr \u003d getStyleInstruction(style);\\n\\n  const systemPrompt \u003d `\\n    You are an AI Professor at a Visual Learning Academy.\\n    Topic: \\\"${topic}\\\"\\n    Department: ${subjectInstr}\\n    Academic Level: ${levelInstr}\\n    \\n    Goal: Research this topic using Google Search and create a lesson plan for a high-fidelity educational infographic.\\n    \\n    Structure your response as follows:\\n    \\n    FACTS:\\n    - [Key Learning Objective 1]\\n    - [Critical Process/Step 2]\\n    - [Important Context/Historical Note 3]\\n    - [Key Vocabulary Term with Definition]\\n    \\n    IMAGE_PROMPT:\\n    [Describe a masterwork educational visual. It should clearly explain the topic visually. Include layout details (e.g., \\\"central diagram with radiating labels\\\", \\\"side-by-side comparison\\\"). Ensure it adheres to the ${styleInstr}. Mention the language for any text elements is ${language}. No citations in prompt.]\\n  `;\\n\\n  const response \u003d await getAi().models.generateContent({\\n    model: TEXT_MODEL,\\n    contents: systemPrompt,\\n    config: {\\n      tools: [{ googleSearch: {} }],\\n    },\\n  });\\n\\n  const text \u003d response.text || \\\"\\\";\\n  \\n  const factsMatch \u003d text.match(/FACTS:\\\\s*([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)(?\u003dIMAGE_PROMPT:|$)/i);\\n  const factsRaw \u003d factsMatch ? factsMatch[1].trim() : \\\"\\\";\\n  const facts \u003d factsRaw.split(\u0027\\\\n\u0027)\\n    .map(f \u003d\u003e f.replace(/^-\\\\s*/, \u0027\u0027).trim())\\n    .filter(f \u003d\u003e f.length \u003e 0)\\n    .slice(0, 5);\\n\\n  const promptMatch \u003d text.match(/IMAGE_PROMPT:\\\\s*([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)$/i);\\n  const imagePrompt \u003d promptMatch ? promptMatch[1].trim() : `Create a detailed educational infographic about ${topic} in a ${style} style for ${level} level.`;\\n\\n  const searchResults: SearchResultItem[] \u003d [];\\n  const chunks \u003d response.candidates?.[0]?.groundingMetadata?.groundingChunks;\\n  \\n  if (chunks) {\\n    chunks.forEach(chunk \u003d\u003e {\\n      if (chunk.web?.uri \u0026\u0026 chunk.web?.title) {\\n        searchResults.push({ title: chunk.web.title, url: chunk.web.uri });\\n      }\\n    });\\n  }\\n\\n  const uniqueResults \u003d Array.from(new Map(searchResults.map(item \u003d\u003e [item.url, item])).values());\\n\\n  return {\\n    imagePrompt,\\n    facts,\\n    searchResults: uniqueResults\\n  };\\n};\\n\\nexport const generateInfographicImage \u003d async (prompt: string): Promise\u003cstring\u003e \u003d\u003e {\\n  const response \u003d await getAi().models.generateContent({\\n    model: IMAGE_MODEL,\\n    contents: { parts: [{ text: prompt }] },\\n    config: { responseModalities: [Modality.IMAGE] }\\n  });\\n\\n  const part \u003d response.candidates?.[0]?.content?.parts?.find(p \u003d\u003e p.inlineData);\\n  if (part \u0026\u0026 part.inlineData \u0026\u0026 part.inlineData.data) {\\n    return `data:image/png;base64,${part.inlineData.data}`;\\n  }\\n  throw new Error(\\\"Failed to generate educational visual.\\\");\\n};\\n\\nexport const editInfographicImage \u003d async (currentImageBase64: string, editInstruction: string): Promise\u003cstring\u003e \u003d\u003e {\\n  const cleanBase64 \u003d currentImageBase64.replace(/^data:image\\\\/(png|jpeg|jpg);base64,/, \u0027\u0027);\\n  \\n  const response \u003d await getAi().models.generateContent({\\n    model: EDIT_MODEL,\\n    contents: {\\n      parts: [\\n         { inlineData: { mimeType: \u0027image/jpeg\u0027, data: cleanBase64 } },\\n         { text: `Educational Correction: ${editInstruction}. Maintain the pedagogical clarity and existing style.` }\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    config: { responseModalities: [Modality.IMAGE] }\\n  });\\n  \\n  const part \u003d response.candidates?.[0]?.content?.parts?.find(p \u003d\u003e p.inlineData);\\n  if (part \u0026\u0026 part.inlineData \u0026\u0026 part.inlineData.data) {\\n    return `data:image/png;base64,${part.inlineData.data}`;\\n  }\\n  throw new Error(\\\"Modification failed.\\\");\\n};\\n\"}]},{\"path\":\"App.tsx\",\"generationType\":1,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"Overhauled UI to emphasize the \\\"Academy\\\" and \\\"Subject\\\" focus. Added SubjectArea state and UI controls.\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"\\n/**\\n * @license\\n * SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0\\n*/\\nimport React, { useState, useEffect } from \u0027react\u0027;\\nimport { GeneratedImage, ComplexityLevel, VisualStyle, Language, SearchResultItem, SubjectArea } from \u0027./types\u0027;\\nimport { \\n  researchTopicForPrompt, \\n  generateInfographicImage, \\n  editInfographicImage,\\n} from \u0027./services/geminiService\u0027;\\nimport Infographic from \u0027./components/Infographic\u0027;\\nimport Loading from \u0027./components/Loading\u0027;\\nimport IntroScreen from \u0027./components/IntroScreen\u0027;\\nimport SearchResults from \u0027./components/SearchResults\u0027;\\nimport { Search, AlertCircle, History, GraduationCap, Palette, Microscope, Atom, Compass, Globe, Sun, Moon, Key, CreditCard, ExternalLink, DollarSign, BookOpen, FlaskConical, Languages, Calculator, LandPlot, Zap } from \u0027lucide-react\u0027;\\n\\nconst App: React.FC \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\\n  const [showIntro, setShowIntro] \u003d useState(true);\\n  const [topic, setTopic] \u003d useState(\u0027\u0027);\\n  const [complexityLevel, setComplexityLevel] \u003d useState\u003cComplexityLevel\u003e(\u0027High School\u0027);\\n  const [visualStyle, setVisualStyle] \u003d useState\u003cVisualStyle\u003e(\u0027Default\u0027);\\n  const [language, setLanguage] \u003d useState\u003cLanguage\u003e(\u0027English\u0027);\\n  const [subject, setSubject] \u003d useState\u003cSubjectArea\u003e(\u0027STEM\u0027);\\n  \\n  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [loadingMessage, setLoadingMessage] \u003d useState(\u0027\u0027);\\n  const [loadingStep, setLoadingStep] \u003d useState\u003cnumber\u003e(0);\\n  const [loadingFacts, setLoadingFacts] \u003d useState\u003cstring[]\u003e([]);\\n  const [error, setError] \u003d useState\u003cstring | null\u003e(null);\\n  \\n  const [imageHistory, setImageHistory] \u003d useState\u003cGeneratedImage[]\u003e([]);\\n  const [currentSearchResults, setCurrentSearchResults] \u003d useState\u003cSearchResultItem[]\u003e([]);\\n  const [isDarkMode, setIsDarkMode] \u003d useState(true);\\n\\n  // API Key State\\n  const [hasApiKey, setHasApiKey] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [checkingKey, setCheckingKey] \u003d useState(true);\\n\\n  useEffect(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (isDarkMode) {\\n      document.documentElement.classList.add(\u0027dark\u0027);\\n    } else {\\n      document.documentElement.classList.remove(\u0027dark\u0027);\\n    }\\n  }, [isDarkMode]);\\n\\n  useEffect(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    const checkKey \u003d async () \u003d\u003e {\\n      try {\\n        if (window.aistudio \u0026\u0026 window.aistudio.hasSelectedApiKey) {\\n          const hasKey \u003d await window.aistudio.hasSelectedApiKey();\\n          setHasApiKey(hasKey);\\n        } else {\\n          setHasApiKey(true);\\n        }\\n      } catch (e) {\\n        console.error(\\\"Error checking API key:\\\", e);\\n      } finally {\\n        setCheckingKey(false);\\n      }\\n    };\\n    checkKey();\\n  }, []);\\n\\n  const handleSelectKey \u003d async () \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (window.aistudio \u0026\u0026 window.aistudio.openSelectKey) {\\n      try {\\n        await window.aistudio.openSelectKey();\\n        setHasApiKey(true);\\n        setError(null);\\n      } catch (e) {\\n        console.error(\\\"Failed to open key selector:\\\", e);\\n      }\\n    }\\n  };\\n\\n  const handleGenerate \u003d async (e: React.FormEvent) \u003d\u003e {\\n    e.preventDefault();\\n    if (isLoading) return;\\n\\n    if (!topic.trim()) {\\n        setError(\\\"Please specify a lesson topic.\\\");\\n        return;\\n    }\\n\\n    setIsLoading(true);\\n    setError(null);\\n    setLoadingStep(1);\\n    setLoadingFacts([]);\\n    setCurrentSearchResults([]);\\n    setLoadingMessage(`Consulting Department: ${subject}...`);\\n\\n    try {\\n      const researchResult \u003d await researchTopicForPrompt(topic, complexityLevel, visualStyle, language, subject);\\n      \\n      setLoadingFacts(researchResult.facts);\\n      setCurrentSearchResults(researchResult.searchResults);\\n      \\n      setLoadingStep(2);\\n      setLoadingMessage(`Rendering Educational Visual...`);\\n      \\n      let base64Data \u003d await generateInfographicImage(researchResult.imagePrompt);\\n      \\n      const newImage: GeneratedImage \u003d {\\n        id: Date.now().toString(),\\n        data: base64Data,\\n        prompt: topic,\\n        timestamp: Date.now(),\\n        level: complexityLevel,\\n        style: visualStyle,\\n        language: language,\\n        subject: subject\\n      };\\n\\n      setImageHistory([newImage, ...imageHistory]);\\n    } catch (err: any) {\\n      console.error(err);\\n      if (err.message \u0026\u0026 (err.message.includes(\\\"Requested entity was not found\\\") || err.message.includes(\\\"404\\\") || err.message.includes(\\\"403\\\"))) {\\n          setError(\\\"Session expired or billing required. Please re-select your academy access key.\\\");\\n          setHasApiKey(false);\\n      } else {\\n          setError(\u0027The academy systems are temporarily offline. Please try again.\u0027);\\n      }\\n    } finally {\\n      setIsLoading(false);\\n      setLoadingStep(0);\\n    }\\n  };\\n\\n  const handleEdit \u003d async (editPrompt: string) \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (imageHistory.length \u003d\u003d\u003d 0) return;\\n    const currentImage \u003d imageHistory[0];\\n    setIsLoading(true);\\n    setError(null);\\n    setLoadingStep(2);\\n    setLoadingMessage(`Applying Correction: \\\"${editPrompt}\\\"...`);\\n\\n    try {\\n      const base64Data \u003d await editInfographicImage(currentImage.data, editPrompt);\\n      const newImage: GeneratedImage \u003d {\\n        id: Date.now().toString(),\\n        data: base64Data,\\n        prompt: editPrompt,\\n        timestamp: Date.now(),\\n        level: currentImage.level,\\n        style: currentImage.style,\\n        language: currentImage.language,\\n        subject: currentImage.subject\\n      };\\n      setImageHistory([newImage, ...imageHistory]);\\n    } catch (err: any) {\\n      console.error(err);\\n      setError(\u0027Visual modification failed. Please try a simpler correction.\u0027);\\n    } finally {\\n      setIsLoading(false);\\n      setLoadingStep(0);\\n    }\\n  };\\n\\n  const restoreImage \u003d (img: GeneratedImage) \u003d\u003e {\\n     const newHistory \u003d imageHistory.filter(i \u003d\u003e i.id !\u003d\u003d img.id);\\n     setImageHistory([img, ...newHistory]);\\n  };\\n\\n  const subjects: {id: SubjectArea, icon: any, label: string, color: string}[] \u003d [\\n    {id: \u0027STEM\u0027, icon: FlaskConical, label: \u0027STEM\u0027, color: \u0027text-cyan-500\u0027},\\n    {id: \u0027History\u0027, icon: ScrollText, label: