fined, or, if not defined, how to best implement them!\\n\\n\\n**Implementing handleRegenerate**\\n\\nI\u0027ve made progress on `handleRegenerate`. It\u0027s clear I need to define it within `App.tsx` because it\u0027s passed as a prop to the `Infographic` component. It should likely interact with the Gemini service to fetch a new image based on the current topic, selected level, and style. I\u0027ve also identified that `Square` and `Play` are missing from the `lucide-react` imports and I\u0027ll add them to the import statement.\\n\\n\\n**Adding Regeneration Logic**\\n\\nI\u0027ve successfully implemented `handleRegenerate` now. It constructs a prompt based on the chosen level, style, and topic, then calls `generateInfographicImage` to fetch new image data and updates the current slide. It also includes basic error handling. I also noticed that the `onEdit` handler is an empty function, but I decided to focus on resolving the original error and leave it for later.\\n\\n\\n**Reviewing App.tsx Code**\\n\\nI\u0027m revisiting `App.tsx`, focusing on the recent additions. I\u0027ve successfully added `handleRegenerate` function and ensured it\u0027s correctly passed as a prop. I also verified that `Square` and `Play` are imported from `lucide-react`. I then looked into `geminiService.ts` to make sure `generateInfographicImage` handles the API key and it does! I checked how `getAi` from `geminiService.ts` uses `process.env.API_KEY`, following the guidelines on best usage of the API.\\n\\n\\n**Verifying API Key Availability**\\n\\nI\u0027ve added a check for the API key availability within `handleRegenerate` now. Before generating the infographic, the application ensures `hasSelectedApiKey()` returns true. If not, it prompts the user to select an API key using `window.aistudio.openSelectKey()`. I\u0027ve updated the error handling to include a check for the \\\"Requested entity was not found\\\" error, prompting the user for an API key if this occurs. I\u0027m focusing on these requested items and leaving the edit handler for now.\\n\\n\\n**Refactoring App.tsx**\\n\\nNow, I\u0027m refactoring `App.tsx` further. I\u0027ve integrated `Play` and `Square` into the `lucide-react` import statement, resolving that particular compilation error. I\u0027ve also implemented the `handleRegenerate` function, aligning it with the expected functionality to fetch new image data. I\u0027m satisfied that the initial error related to imports is resolved. Now, on to testing!\\n\\n\\n**Adding lucide-react Imports**\\n\\nI\u0027ve updated the `lucide-react` import statement to include the necessary icons: `Hand`, `Volume2`, `Menu`, `X`, `Award`, `CheckCircle2`, `Sparkles`, `ShieldCheck`, `GraduationCap`, `ArrowLeft`, `UserCircle`, `MapPin`, `Book`, `Heart`, `Play`, and `Square`. I\u0027ve made sure to remove the old redundant imports. This should address the remaining issues from the previous phase!\\n\\n\\n**Organizing Component State**\\n\\nI\u0027m currently organizing the component state. I\u0027ve noted the `useState` hooks for `studentProfile` (loading from local storage) and `enrollForm`. I\u0027m also setting up `useRef` hooks for audio context, session management, and timer to handle playback and state. The initial topics for the course are set as well.\\n\\n\\n**Updating Course Topic State**\\n\\nI\u0027m now integrating new course topics and managing their locked/unlocked states based on student tier. I\u0027ve added new topics. I\u0027m dynamically updating the `topics` state within the `useEffect` hook, which now reflects the locking mechanism based on whether a student tier is \\\"Grandmaster\\\" or \\\"Scholar\\\".\\n\\n\\n**Integrating API Key Check**\\n\\nI\u0027m now incorporating an API key check into the course topic state management. I\u0027m adding logic to ensure an API key has been selected before unlocking the course topics. The `useEffect` hook now updates the `topics` state based on API key availability and student tier. This makes sure course materials are only unlocked when the prerequisites are met.\\n\\n\\n\\n**Establishing Lecture Session**\\n\\nI\u0027m now focusing on establishing a lecture session. I\u0027ve added a check for the API key availability before starting the lecture. If no key is present, it prompts the user to select one. Upon a successful key selection, the audio context is created. I\u0027m moving toward handling the audio stream and setting up the script processor to prepare for the session connection. This involves creating audio contexts and capturing the microphone stream.\\n\\n\\n\\n**Establishing Audio Playback**\\n\\nI\u0027m now implementing the audio playback mechanism. I\u0027m focusing on the `onmessage` handler, which deals with incoming audio data from the server. If audio data arrives as base64, I decode it and create an audio buffer. I\u0027ve set up logic for timing the start of each audio segment to make sure it plays smoothly and that playback timing avoids overlap and interruptions. I also handle the interruption signal from the server to stop all active audio sources to avoid any conflicts.\\n\\n\\n**Managing Tool Call Responses**\\n\\nI\u0027m now integrating the `render_visual` function call response. I\u0027ve successfully implemented the logic within the `onmessage` handler to process incoming `toolCall` messages. I\u0027m handling the response for visual aids, which includes calling `generateInfographicImage` to fetch image data using the description from the function call arguments. I have added error handling, which opens the API key selection modal if the \\\"Requested entity was not found\\\" error is thrown. I\u0027m making sure to send a response back to the session with the new image.\\n\\n\\n**Implementing Audio Stream**\\n\\nI\u0027m now focused on the audio stream for the lecture session. I\u0027ve set up the logic within the `onmessage` handler to decode and play audio. I\u0027m focusing on refining the audio buffer creation and its timing to ensure smooth playback, especially handling the interruption signals from the server to prevent overlapping sounds and disruptions in the lectures. I\u0027m also ensuring all audio sources pause when an interruption signal arrives.\\n\\n\\n**Managing Auth Views**\\n\\nI\u0027m now implementing the authentication flow, beginning with a redirect. I\u0027m building out the intro, auth, and dashboard view management logic. I\u0027ve built the `IntroScreen` and have implemented `auth` and `dashboard` in this control structure. I\u0027m focusing on user interactions and how to transition among the views based on user actions.\\n\\n\\n\\n**Structuring Authentication Flow**\\n\\nI\u0027m now focused on the authentication flow, specifically structuring the Intro, Auth, and Dashboard views. I\u0027m building out logic for these different views. I have built out `IntroScreen`. Next, I will be working on `auth` and `dashboard` components in the control structure. My focus is on handling user interactions and seamlessly transitioning between views according to user input.\\n\\n\\n\\n**Structuring Enroll Flow**\\n\\nI\u0027m now implementing the enrollment flow, building out the \u0027enroll\u0027 view, including a back button to the \u0027auth\u0027 screen. I\u0027m focusing on user interface elements and data capture within this section. This will allow the user to provide their background, and then the system can curate a perfect learning path. I\u0027m focusing on the user interface.\\n\\n\\n**Implementing Enroll Flow**\\n\\nI\u0027m now integrating the enrollment flow, starting with data capture. I\u0027ve built the interface elements and hooked up a basic `enroll` view. I\u0027m focusing on user input now: including the required academic name field in the enrollment form and integrating validation. I\u0027m making sure to implement and integrate the form submission handler, along with a back button.\\n\\n\\n**Refining Enroll Data Capture**\\n\\nI\u0027m now refining the enrollment data capture. I\u0027ve focused on adding validation to the form fields, specifically for the academic name. I also ensured that all form input elements work as expected and that the form submission is hooked up. Finally, I\u0027m working to make sure the \\\"back\\\" button functions as intended.\\n\\n\\n**Integrating Enrollment Data**\\n\\nI\u0027m now integrating the data from the enrollment form. I\u0027m focusing on capturing the user\u0027s intended study area using a `\u003cselect\u003e` element populated with relevant options. I am also making sure that the form\u0027s state is updated correctly with the selected value, and that the appropriate styles and classes are applied to the element.\\n\\n\\n**Refining Form Integration**\\n\\nI\u0027m now focusing on refining the enrollment form. I\u0027ve successfully integrated the `\u003cselect\u003e` element to capture the user\u0027s study area. I\u0027m verifying the form state updates correctly with the selected value, while ensuring that the relevant styles are applied. I\u0027m now making sure that the final submit is integrated.\\n\\n\\n**Updating Sidebar Implementation**\\n\\nI\u0027m now implementing the sidebar. I\u0027ve focused on integrating the opening and closing state with the main application view. I\u0027ve integrated this into the main component and am making sure the close button in the sidebar works. I\u0027m focusing on ensuring the user can open and close the sidebar and that the overall layout is responsive.\\n\\n\\n**Implementing Sidebar State**\\n\\nI\u0027m now integrating the sidebar\u0027s open/close state with the application view. The sidebar\u0027s state controls the visibility and responsiveness of the application layout. The close button is working. Next, I am working on the overall layout.\\n\\n\\n**Implementing Sidebar State**\\n\\nI\u0027ve integrated the sidebar\u0027s open/close state, using `${isSidebarOpen ? \u0027translate-x-0\u0027 : \u0027translate-x-full\u0027}` to control its visibility and responsiveness in the application layout. The close button is working to close the sidebar. I\u0027m now fine-tuning the overall layout to make sure that it\u0027s all working.\\n\\n\\n**Implementing Dashboard Transition**\\n\\nI\u0027m now integrating the dashboard transition. Specifically, I\u0027m working on the button within the lecture view, which calls `setView(\u0027dashboard\u0027)`. This button takes the user back to the dashboard, and I\u0027m ensuring this navigation is smooth.\\n\\n\\n**Integrating Audio Visuals**\\n\\nI\u0027m currently working to integrate the audio and visuals seamlessly within the lecture session. I\u0027m focusing on the `LectureView` component, ensuring the correct icons render. I\u0027m focusing on incorporating the `volume` icon, as well as the audio volume, to refine the visual cues related to audio playback to increase immersion for the user. I\u0027m making sure to address these integrations as the main focus now.\\n\\n\\n**Enhancing Visual Cues**\\n\\nI\u0027m now enhancing the visual cues for the lecture. I\u0027ve focused on integrating the `Sparkles` icon to visually indicate lecture status. I\u0027m ensuring the correct icons render and refining the implementation of `volume`, including audio volume controls. The goal is to provide seamless visual feedback to increase user engagement.\\n\\n\\n**Refining Microphone Visuals**\\n\\nI\u0027m now refining the visual elements related to the microphone input within the lecture. I\u0027m focusing on the `Mic` and `Hand` icons and their visual representations. The goal is to provide intuitive feedback to the user regarding the state of the microphone, whether it\u0027s active or inactive. I\u0027m making sure to implement and integrate the form submission handler, along with a back button.\\n\\n\\n**Enhancing Lecture Controls**\\n\\nI\u0027m currently working on enhancing the lecture controls within the application. I\u0027m focusing on the `ExamMode` toggle, which conditionally renders `Square` or `Play` icons. I\u0027m also addressing the text displayed on the button, which is either \u0027STOP SESSION\u0027 or \u0027START STUDY\u0027. I want to make sure it functions correctly based on both `isLecturing` and `isExamMode` state, which drives a smooth experience for the user.\\n\\n\\n\",\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767889602,\"nanos\":456000000},\"doneTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767889643,\"nanos\":837000000}},{\"id\":228,\"author\":\"model\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"generationTable\",\"entries\":[{\"path\":\"App.tsx\",\"generationType\":2,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"Add missing imports (Square, Play) and implement handleRegenerate function to fix compilation errors.\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"\\n/**\\n * @license\\n * SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0\\n*/\\nimport React, { useState, useEffect, useRef } from \u0027react\u0027;\\nimport { GeneratedImage, ComplexityLevel, VisualStyle, Language, SubjectArea, CourseTopic, StudentProfile, SubscriptionTier } from \u0027./types\u0027;\\nimport { connectLecturer, generateInfographicImage } from \u0027./services/geminiService\u0027;\\nimport { decode, decodeAudioData, createBlob } from \u0027./services/audioService\u0027;\\nimport Infographic from \u0027./components/Infographic\u0027;\\nimport Syllabus from \u0027./components/Syllabus\u0027;\\nimport IntroScreen from \u0027./components/IntroScreen\u0027;\\n// Added Play and Square to the imports from lucide-react to fix missing name errors.\\nimport { Sun, Moon, Mic, Hand, Volume2, Menu, X, Award, CheckCircle2, Sparkles, ShieldCheck, GraduationCap, ArrowLeft, UserCircle, MapPin, Book, Heart, Play, Square } from \u0027lucide-react\u0027;\\n\\ntype ViewState \u003d \u0027intro\u0027 | \u0027auth\u0027 | \u0027enroll\u0027 | \u0027dashboard\u0027 | \u0027class\u0027;\\n\\nconst App: React.FC \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\\n  const [view, setView] \u003d useState\u003cViewState\u003e(\u0027intro\u0027);\\n  const [currentTopic, setCurrentTopic] \u003d useState\u003cstring\u003e(\u0027Indigenous Worldviews\u0027);\\n  const [complexityLevel, setComplexityLevel] \u003d useState\u003cComplexityLevel\u003e(\u0027High School\u0027);\\n  const [visualStyle, setVisualStyle] \u003d useState\u003cVisualStyle\u003e(\u0027Realistic\u0027);\\n  \\n  const [isLecturing, setIsLecturing] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [isQuestioning, setIsQuestioning] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [currentSlide, setCurrentSlide] \u003d useState\u003cGeneratedImage | null\u003e(null);\\n  const [isDarkMode, setIsDarkMode] \u003d useState(true);\\n  const [isSidebarOpen, setIsSidebarOpen] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [isExamMode, setIsExamMode] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [showPromotion, setShowPromotion] \u003d useState(false);\\n\\n  const [student, setStudent] \u003d useState\u003cStudentProfile | null\u003e(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    const saved \u003d localStorage.getItem(\u0027student_profile\u0027);\\n    return saved ? JSON.parse(saved) : null;\\n  });\\n\\n  // Enrollment form state\\n  const [enrollForm, setEnrollForm] \u003d useState({\\n    name: \u0027\u0027,\\n    address: \u0027\u0027,\\n    pastEducation: \u0027\u0027,\\n    major: \u0027History\u0027 as SubjectArea,\\n    tier: \u0027Standard\u0027 as SubscriptionTier\\n  });\\n\\n  // Audio refs\\n  const audioContextRef \u003d useRef\u003cAudioContext | null\u003e(null);\\n  const outputAudioContextRef \u003d useRef\u003cAudioContext | null\u003e(null);\\n  const sessionRef \u003d useRef\u003cany\u003e(null);\\n  const nextStartTimeRef \u003d useRef(0);\\n  const sourcesRef \u003d useRef\u003cSet\u003cAudioBufferSourceNode\u003e\u003e(new Set());\\n  const studyTimerRef \u003d useRef\u003cnumber | null\u003e(null);\\n\\n  const [topics, setTopics] \u003d useState\u003cCourseTopic[]\u003e([\\n    { id: \u00271\u0027, title: \u0027Indigenous Worldviews\u0027, duration: \u00271.2 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: \u0027History\u0027 },\\n    { id: \u00272\u0027, title: \u0027Astrophysics \u0026 Navigation\u0027, duration: \u00272.5 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: \u0027Astronomy\u0027, isLocked: true },\\n    { id: \u00273\u0027, title: \u0027Architectural Engineering\u0027, duration: \u00271.8 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: \u0027Engineering\u0027, isLocked: true },\\n    { id: \u00274\u0027, title: \u0027The Philosophy of Mind\u0027, duration: \u00272.0 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: \u0027Philosophy\u0027, isLocked: true },\\n    { id: \u00275\u0027, title: \u0027Quantum Archeology\u0027, duration: \u00271.5 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: \u0027Archeology\u0027, isLocked: true },\\n    { id: \u00276\u0027, title: \u0027Ethno-Linguistics\u0027, duration: \u00271.8 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: \u0027Linguistics\u0027, isLocked: true },\\n  ]);\\n\\n  useEffect(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (isDarkMode) document.documentElement.classList.add(\u0027class\u0027, \u0027dark\u0027);\\n    else document.documentElement.classList.remove(\u0027dark\u0027);\\n  }, [isDarkMode]);\\n\\n  useEffect(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (student) {\\n      localStorage.setItem(\u0027student_profile\u0027, JSON.stringify(student));\\n      setTopics(prev \u003d\u003e prev.map(t \u003d\u003e {\\n        if (student.tier \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027Grandmaster\u0027) return { ...t, isLocked: false };\\n        if (student.tier \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027Scholar\u0027) {\\n          return ([\u0027Philosophy\u0027, \u0027Archeology\u0027, \u0027Linguistics\u0027].includes(t.subject)) ? { ...t, isLocked: true } : { ...t, isLocked: false };\\n        }\\n        return ([\u0027History\u0027, \u0027STEM\u0027, \u0027General\u0027].includes(t.subject)) ? { ...t, isLocked: false } : { ...t, isLocked: true };\\n      }));\\n    }\\n  }, [student]);\\n\\n  // Added handleRegenerate to fix the missing name error. This function updates the visual aid based on selected complexity and style.\\n  const handleRegenerate \u003d async (level: ComplexityLevel, style: VisualStyle) \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (!(await window.aistudio.hasSelectedApiKey())) {\\n      await window.aistudio.openSelectKey();\\n    }\\n    setComplexityLevel(level);\\n    setVisualStyle(style);\\n    \\n    const prompt \u003d `Educational visual about ${currentTopic}, ${style} style, ${level} complexity.`;\\n    try {\\n      const data \u003d await generateInfographicImage(prompt);\\n      setCurrentSlide({\\n        id: Date.now().toString(),\\n        data,\\n        prompt: prompt,\\n        timestamp: Date.now(),\\n        level: level,\\n        style: style\\n      });\\n    } catch (e: any) {\\n      if (e?.message?.includes(\\\"Requested entity was not found.\\\")) {\\n        await window.aistudio.openSelectKey();\\n      }\\n      console.error(\\\"Regeneration failed\\\", e);\\n    }\\n  };\\n\\n  const toggleLecture \u003d async (exam: boolean \u003d false) \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (isLecturing) {\\n      sessionRef.current?.close?.();\\n      setIsLecturing(false);\\n      setIsExamMode(false);\\n      return;\\n    }\\n\\n    if (!(await window.aistudio.hasSelectedApiKey())) {\\n      await window.aistudio.openSelectKey();\\n    }\\n\\n    setIsExamMode(exam);\\n\\n    try {\\n      const audioCtx \u003d new (window.AudioContext || (window as any).webkitAudioContext)({ sampleRate: 16000 });\\n      const outputCtx \u003d new (window.AudioContext || (window as any).webkitAudioContext)({ sampleRate: 24000 });\\n      audioContextRef.current \u003d audioCtx;\\n      outputAudioContextRef.current \u003d outputCtx;\\n\\n      const stream \u003d await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ audio: true });\\n      const source \u003d audioCtx.createMediaStreamSource(stream);\\n      const scriptProcessor \u003d audioCtx.createScriptProcessor(4096, 1, 1);\\n\\n      const sessionPromise \u003d connectLecturer({\\n        onopen: () \u003d\u003e {\\n          source.connect(scriptProcessor);\\n          scriptProcessor.connect(audioCtx.destination);\\n        },\\n        onmessage: async (message: any) \u003d\u003e {\\n          const base64Audio \u003d message.serverContent?.modelTurn?.parts[0]?.inlineData?.data;\\n          if (base64Audio \u0026\u0026 outputAudioContextRef.current) {\\n            const ctx \u003d outputAudioContextRef.current;\\n            nextStartTimeRef.current \u003d Math.max(nextStartTimeRef.current, ctx.currentTime);\\n            const audioBuffer \u003d await decodeAudioData(decode(base64Audio), ctx, 24000, 1);\\n            const sourceNode \u003d ctx.createBufferSource();\\n            sourceNode.buffer \u003d audioBuffer;\\n            sourceNode.connect(ctx.destination);\\n            sourceNode.start(nextStartTimeRef.current);\\n            nextStartTimeRef.current +\u003d audioBuffer.duration;\\n            sourcesRef.current.add(sourceNode);\\n            sourceNode.onended \u003d () \u003d\u003e sourcesRef.current.delete(sourceNode);\\n          }\\n\\n          if (message.serverContent?.interrupted) {\\n            sourcesRef.current.forEach(s \u003d\u003e s.stop());\\n            sourcesRef.current.clear();\\n            nextStartTimeRef.current \u003d 0;\\n          }\\n\\n          if (message.toolCall) {\\n            for (const fc of message.toolCall.functionCalls) {\\n              if (fc.name \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027render_visual\u0027) {\\n                try {\\n                  const data \u003d await generateInfographicImage(fc.args.description);\\n                  setCurrentSlide({\\n                    id: Date.now().toString(),\\n                    data,\\n                    prompt: fc.args.description,\\n                    timestamp: Date.now(),\\n                    level: complexityLevel,\\n                    style: visualStyle\\n                  });\\n                  sessionPromise.then(s \u003d\u003e s.sendToolResponse({\\n                    functionResponses: { id: fc.id, name: fc.name, response: { result: \\\"Visual aid updated.\\\" } }\\n                  }));\\n                } catch (e) { \\n                  if (e instanceof Error \u0026\u0026 e.message.includes(\\\"Requested entity was not found.\\\")) {\\n                    await window.aistudio.openSelectKey();\\n                  }\\n                }\\n              }\\n            }\\n          }\\n        },\\n        onerror: (e: any) \u003d\u003e console.error(e),\\n        onclose: () \u003d\u003e { setIsLecturing(false); setIsExamMode(false); }\\n      }, student!, exam ? `FINAL EXAM FOR ${currentTopic}` : currentTopic);\\n\\n      scriptProcessor.onaudioprocess \u003d (e) \u003d\u003e {\\n        if (!isQuestioning \u0026\u0026 !exam) return;\\n        const inputData \u003d e.inputBuffer.getChannelData(0);\\n        const pcmBlob \u003d createBlob(inputData);\\n        sessionPromise.then(session \u003d\u003e session.sendRealtimeInput({ media: pcmBlob }));\\n      };\\n\\n      sessionRef.current \u003d await sessionPromise;\\n      setIsLecturing(true);\\n      setIsSidebarOpen(false);\\n    } catch (e) {\\n      console.error(\\\"Session fail\\\", e);\\n    }\\n  };\\n\\n  const handleEnrollSubmit \u003d (e: React.FormEvent) \u003d\u003e {\\n    e.preventDefault();\\n    if (enrollForm.name) {\\n      const newStudent: StudentProfile \u003d {\\n        ...enrollForm,\\n        level: \u0027Elementary\u0027,\\n        enrolledDate: Date.now(),\\n        studyHoursGoal: 2,\\n        currentStudyHours: 0\\n      };\\n      setStudent(newStudent);\\n      setView(\u0027dashboard\u0027);\\n    }\\n  };\\n\\n  const handleLogout \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\\n    setStudent(null);\\n    localStorage.removeItem(\u0027student_profile\u0027);\\n    setView(\u0027intro\u0027);\\n  };\\n\\n  // Views\\n  if (view \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027intro\u0027) {\\n    return \u003cIntroScreen onComplete\u003d{() \u003d\u003e setView(\u0027auth\u0027)} studentName\u003d{student?.name} /\u003e;\\n  }\\n\\n  if (view \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027auth\u0027) {\\n    return (\\n      \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center bg-slate-950 p-6\\\"\u003e\\n        \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_center,_var(--tw-gradient-stops))] from-cyan-900/20 via-slate-950 to-black pointer-events-none\\\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\\n        \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"relative z-10 w-full max-w-md space-y-8 text-center animate-in fade-in slide-in-from-bottom-4 duration-1000\\\"\u003e\\n           \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"w-20 h-20 bg-cyan-600 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mx-auto shadow-2xl\\\"\u003e\\n              \u003cGraduationCap className\u003d\\\"w-12 h-12 text-white\\\" /\u003e\\n           \u003c/div\u003e\\n           \u003ch2 className\u003d\\\"text-3xl font-display font-bold text-white tracking-tight\\\"\u003eAccess Your Future\u003c/h2\u003e\\n           \u003cp className\u003d\\\"text-slate-400 text-sm\\\"\u003eWelcome back to the Indigenous University of Infinite Vision.\u003c/p\u003e\\n           \\n           \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"space-y-4 pt-8\\\"\u003e\\n              \u003cbutton \\n                onClick\u003d{() \u003d\u003e student ? setView(\u0027dashboard\u0027) : setView(\u0027enroll\u0027)}\\n                className\u003d\\\"w-full py-4 bg-cyan-600 hover:bg-cyan-500 text-white rounded-2xl font-bold transition-all shadow-xl shadow-cyan-600/20 active:scale-95\\\"\\n              \u003e\\n                {student ? `LOG IN AS ${student.name.toUpperCase()}` : \u0027NEW ENROLLMENT\u0027}\\n              \u003c/button\u003e\\n              {!student \u0026\u0026 (\\n                \u003cbutton \\n                   disabled\\n                   className\u003d\\\"w-full py-4 bg-slate-900 text-slate-500 rounded-2xl font-bold border border-white/5 opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed\\\"\\n                \u003e\\n                   LOG IN TO EXISTING ACCOUNT\\n                \u003c/button\u003e\\n              )}\\n              {student \u0026\u0026 (\\n                \u003cbutton \\n                   onClick\u003d{handleLogout}\\n                   className\u003d\\\"text-slate-500 text-xs hover:text-red-500 transition-colors uppercase tracking-widest font-bold\\\"\\n                \u003e\\n                  Switch Profile / Sign Out\\n                \u003c/button\u003e\\n              )}\\n           \u003c/div\u003e\\n        \u003c/div\u003e\\n      \u003c/div\u003e\\n    );\\n  }\\n\\n  if (view \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027enroll\u0027) {\\n    return (\\n      \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"min-h-screen flex flex-col bg-slate-950 p-6 overflow-y-auto custom-scrollbar\\\"\u003e\\n        \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"max-w-xl mx-auto w-full py-12 space-y-12 animate-in fade-in slide-in-from-left-8 duration-700\\\"\u003e\\n           \u003cbutton onClick\u003d{() \u003d\u003e setView(\u0027auth\u0027)} className\u003d\\\"text-slate-500 hover:text-white flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-bold transition-colors\\\"\u003e\\n              \u003cArrowLeft className\u003d\\\"w-4 h-4\\\" /\u003e BACK\\n           \u003c/button\u003e\\n           \\n           \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"space-y-2\\\"\u003e\\n              \u003ch2 className\u003d\\\"text-4xl font-display font-bold text-white leading-tight\\\"\u003eIdentity Registry\u003c/h2\u003e\\n              \u003cp className\u003d\\\"text-slate-400\\\"\u003eOur AI needs your background to curate the perfect learning path.\u003c/p\u003e\\n           \u003c/div\u003e\\n\\n           \u003cform onSubmit\u003d{handleEnrollSubmit} className\u003d\\\"space-y-6\\\"\u003e\\n              \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"grid grid-cols-1 gap-6\\\"\u003e\\n                \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"space-y-2\\\"\u003e\\n                   \u003clabel className\u003d\\\"text-[10px] font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest flex items-center gap-2\\\"\u003e\\n                      \u003cUserCircle className\u003d\\\"w-3 h-3\\\" /\u003e Full Academic Name\\n                   \u003c/label\u003e\\n                   \u003cinput \\n                      required\\n                      type\u003d\\\"text\\\" \\n                      value\u003d{enrollForm.name}\\n                      onChange\u003d{e \u003d\u003e setEnrollForm({...enrollForm, name: e.target.value})}\\n                      className\u003d\\\"w-full bg-slate-900 border border-white/5 rounded-2xl p-4 text-white focus:ring-2 ring-cyan-500 transition-all outline-none\\\" \\n                      placeholder\u003d\\\"e.g. Elena Vostova\\\"\\n                   /\u003e\\n                \u003c/div\u003e\\n                \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"space-y-2\\\"\u003e\\n                   \u003clabel className\u003d\\\"text-[10px] font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest flex items-center gap-2\\\"\u003e\\n                      \u003cMapPin className\u003d\\\"w-3 h-3\\\" /\u003e Geographical Base\\n                   \u003c/label\u003e\\n                   \u003cinput \\n                      type\u003d\\\"text\\\" \\n                      value\u003d{enrollForm.address}\\n                      onChange\u003d{e \u003d\u003e setEnrollForm({...enrollForm, address: e.target.value})}\\n                      className\u003d\\\"w-full bg-slate-900 border border-white/5 rounded-2xl p-4 text-white focus:ring-2 ring-cyan-500 transition-all outline-none\\\" \\n                      placeholder\u003d\\\"City, Country\\\"\\n                   /\u003e\\n                \u003c/div\u003e\\n                \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"space-y-2\\\"\u003e\\n                   \u003clabel className\u003d\\\"text-[10px] font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest flex items-center gap-2\\\"\u003e\\n                      \u003cBook className\u003d\\\"w-3 h-3\\\" /\u003e Past Education Information\\n                   \u003c/label\u003e\\n                   \u003ctextarea \\n                      value\u003d{enrollForm.pastEducation}\\n                      onChange\u003d{e \u003d\u003e setEnrollForm({...enrollForm, pastEducation: e.target.value})}\\n                      className\u003d\\\"w-full bg-slate-900 border border-white/5 rounded-2xl p-4 text-white focus:ring-2 ring-cyan-500 transition-all outline-none h-32 resize-none\\\" \\n                      placeholder\u003d\\\"Degree, major, or area of self-study...\\\"\\n                   /\u003e\\n                \u003c/div\u003e\\n                \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"space-y-2\\\"\u003e\\n                   \u003clabel className\u003d\\\"text-[10px] font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest flex items-center gap-2\\\"\u003e\\n                      \u003cHeart className\u003d\\\"w-3 h-3\\\" /\u003e Intended Area of Study\\n                   \u003c/label\u003e\\n                   \u003cselect \\n                      value\u003d{enrollForm.major}\\n                      onChange\u003d{e \u003d\u003e setEnrollForm({...enrollForm, major: e.target.value as SubjectArea})}\\n                      className\u003d\\\"w-full bg-slate-900 border border-white/5 rounded-2xl p-4 text-white focus:ring-2 ring-cyan-500 transition-all outline-none\\\"\\n                   \u003e\\n                      \u003coption value\u003d\\\"History\\\"\u003eIndigenous History \u0026 Worldviews\u003c/option\u003e\\n                      \u003coption value\u003d\\\"Astronomy\\\"\u003eAstro-Navigation\u003c/option\u003e\\n                      \u003coption value\u003d\\\"Philosophy\\\"\u003eMetaphysics \u0026 Logic\u003c/option\u003e\\n                      \u003coption value\u003d\\\"Engineering\\\"\u003eFuture Archeology\u003c/option\u003e\\n                      \u003coption value\u003d\\\"STEM\\\"\u003eInterstellar STEM\u003c/option\u003e\\n                   \u003c/select\u003e\\n                \u003c/div\u003e\\n              \u003c/div\u003e\\n\\n              \u003cbutton type\u003d\\\"submit\\\" className\u003d\\\"w-full py-5 bg-white text-slate-950 font-bold rounded-2xl hover:scale-[1.02] active:scale-95 transition-all shadow-2xl\\\"\u003e\\n                COMPLETE ENROLLMENT\\n              \u003c/button\u003e\\n           \u003c/form\u003e\\n        \u003c/div\u003e\\n      \u003c/div\u003e\\n    );\\n  }\\n\\n  // Dashboard (The core request: only one button \\\"Menu\\\")\\n  if (view \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027dashboard\u0027) {\\n    return (\\n      \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center bg-slate-950 relative overflow-hidden\\\"\u003e\\n        \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_bottom_left,_var(--tw-gradient-stops))] from-indigo-900/20 via-slate-950 to-black\\\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\\n        \\n        {/* Ambient background icons */}\\n        \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"absolute inset-0 opacity-10 pointer-events-none\\\"\u003e\\n           \u003cGraduationCap className\u003d\\\"absolute top-20 left-20 w-32 h-32 rotate-12\\\" /\u003e\\n           \u003cShieldCheck className\u003d\\\"absolute bottom-20 right-20 w-40 h-40 -rotate-12\\\" /\u003e\\n        \u003c/div\u003e\\n\\n        \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"relative z-10 flex flex-col items-center gap-12 text-center px-6\\\"\u003e\\n           \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"space-y-4\\\"\u003e\\n              \u003ch1 className\u003d\\\"text-5xl font-display font-bold text-white tracking-tighter\\\"\u003e\\n                 Vision \u003cspan className\u003d\\\"text-cyan-500\\\"\u003eTerminal\u003c/span\u003e\\n              \u003c/h1\u003e\\n              \u003cp className\u003d\\\"text-slate-400 font-medium max-w-sm mx-auto\\\"\u003e\\n                 Welcome, \u003cspan className\u003d\\\"text-cyan-400\\\"\u003e{student?.name}\u003c/span\u003e. Your personalized learning cluster is active.\\n              \u003c/p\u003e\\n           \u003c/div\u003e\\n\\n           \u003cbutton \\n              onClick\u003d{() \u003d\u003e setIsSidebarOpen(true)}\\n              className\u003d\\\"group relative w-56 h-56 rounded-full flex flex-col items-center justify-center transition-all hover:scale-105\\\"\\n           \u003e\\n              \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"absolute inset-0 bg-cyan-600 rounded-full blur-2xl opacity-20 group-hover:opacity-40 animate-pulse\\\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\\n              \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"relative z-10 w-full h-full bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 rounded-full border-8 border-cyan-600/20 flex flex-col items-center justify-center shadow-2xl\\\"\u003e\\n                 \u003cMenu className\u003d\\\"w-16 h-16 text-cyan-500 mb-2 transition-transform group-hover:rotate-90\\\" /\u003e\\n                 \u003cspan className\u003d\\\"text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-[0.4em] group-hover:text-cyan-400\\\"\u003eMenu\u003c/span\u003e\\n              \u003c/div\u003e\\n           \u003c/button\u003e\\n        \u003c/div\u003e\\n\\n        {/* The Sidebar Menu Overlay */}\\n        \u003cdiv className\u003d{`fixed inset-0 z-50 transition-all duration-500 ${isSidebarOpen ? \u0027opacity-100\u0027 : \u0027opacity-0 pointer-events-none\u0027}`}\u003e\\n            \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"absolute inset-0 bg-slate-950/80 backdrop-blur-xl\\\" onClick\u003d{() \u003d\u003e setIsSidebarOpen(false)}\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\\n            \u003cdiv className\u003d{`absolute inset-y-0 right-0 w-full max-w-sm bg-slate-900 shadow-[0_0_100px_rgba(0,0,0,0.5)] border-l border-white/5 transition-transform duration-500 transform ${isSidebarOpen ? \u0027translate-x-0\u0027 : \u0027translate-x-full\u0027}`}\u003e\\n               \u003cSyllabus \\n                  topics\u003d{topics} \\n                  currentId\u003d{topics.find(t \u003d\u003e t.title \u003d\u003d\u003d currentTopic)?.id || \u00271\u0027} \\n                  onSelect\u003d{(t) \u003d\u003e { setCurrentTopic(t.title); setIsSidebarOpen(false); setView(\u0027class\u0027); }} \\n                  onDone\u003d{() \u003d\u003e {}}\\n                  isLecturing\u003d{isLecturing}\\n                  toggleLecture\u003d{toggleLecture}\\n                  student\u003d{student}\\n                  onEnroll\u003d{() \u003d\u003e {}} // not used in this view\\n                  onTopicChange\u003d{setCurrentTopic}\\n                  onPromote\u003d{() \u003d\u003e {}}\\n                  isExamMode\u003d{isExamMode}\\n                  onUpdateTier\u003d{() \u003d\u003e {}}\\n                  onLogout\u003d{handleLogout}\\n                  onClose\u003d{() \u003d\u003e setIsSidebarOpen(false)}\\n               /\u003e\\n            \u003c/div\u003e\\n        \u003c/div\u003e\\n\\n        \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"absolute bottom-8 text-[10px] text-slate-700 uppercase tracking-widest font-bold\\\"\u003e\\n           Indigenous University Academic Terminal\\n        \u003c/div\u003e\\n      \u003c/div\u003e\\n    );\\n  }\\n\\n  // Lecture / Class View\\n  return (\\n    \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"min-h-screen flex flex-col bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-950 text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-200 font-sans transition-colors overflow-hidden\\\"\u003e\\n      \u003cbutton \\n        onClick\u003d{() \u003d\u003e setView(\u0027dashboard\u0027)}\\n        className\u003d\\\"fixed top-6 left-6 z-[60] p-4 bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 rounded-2xl shadow-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-white/10 hover:scale-105 active:scale-95 transition-all text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400\\\"\\n      \u003e\\n        \u003cArrowLeft className\u003d\\\"w-6 h-6\\\" /\u003e\\n      \u003c/button\u003e\\n\\n      \u003cmain className\u003d\\\"flex-1 flex flex-col items-center justify-center p-8 relative\\\"\u003e\\n        \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"max-w-5xl w-full flex flex-col items-center gap-12\\\"\u003e\\n            \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"w-full relative\\\"\u003e\\n               {currentSlide ? (\\n                  \u003cInfographic \\n                    image\u003d{currentSlide} \\n                    onEdit\u003d{() \u003d\u003e {}} \\n                    onRegenerate\u003d{handleRegenerate}\\n                    isEditing\u003d{false}\\n                  /\u003e\\n               ) : (\\n                  \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"aspect-video w-full bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 rounded-[3rem] border border-slate-200 dark:border-white/5 shadow-2xl flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-6 group\\\"\u003e\\n                    \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"relative\\\"\u003e\\n                      \u003cVolume2 className\u003d\\\"w-20 h-20 opacity-10 group-hover:opacity-20 transition-opacity\\\" /\u003e\\n                      {isLecturing \u0026\u0026 \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"absolute inset-0 border-2 border-cyan-500 rounded-full animate-ping opacity-20\\\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e}\\n                    \u003c/div\u003e\\n                    \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"text-center space-y-2 opacity-30\\\"\u003e\\n                        \u003cp className\u003d\\\"font-display font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-sm\\\"\u003e{currentTopic}\u003c/p\u003e\\n                        \u003cp className\u003d\\\"text-xs italic\\\"\u003e{isLecturing ? \\\"Professor Alpha is preparing insights...\\\" : \\\"Start the study session from the bottom controls\\\"}\u003c/p\u003e\\n                    \u003c/div\u003e\\n                  \u003c/div\u003e\\n               )}\\n\\n               {isLecturing \u0026\u0026 (\\n                 \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"absolute top-6 right-6 flex items-center gap-2 bg-emerald-500/90 backdrop-blur-md text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-[10px] font-bold shadow-lg\\\"\u003e\\n                    \u003cSparkles className\u003d\\\"w-3 h-3 animate-pulse\\\" /\u003e\\n                    {isExamMode ? \u0027EXAMINATION IN SESSION\u0027 : \u0027LECTURE IN PROGRESS\u0027}\\n                 \u003c/div\u003e\\n               )}\\n            \u003c/div\u003e\\n\\n            \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"relative\\\"\u003e\\n               \u003cbutton \\n                  onClick\u003d{() \u003d\u003e setIsQuestioning(!isQuestioning)}\\n                  disabled\u003d{!isLecturing || isExamMode}\\n                  className\u003d{`flex flex-col items-center justify-center w-40 h-40 rounded-full border-8 transition-all disabled:opacity-20 disabled:scale-90 ${\\n                    isQuestioning \\n                    ? \u0027bg-amber-500 border-amber-400 scale-110 shadow-[0_0_50px_rgba(245,158,11,0.4)] text-white\u0027 \\n                    : \u0027bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 border-white dark:border-slate-800 text-slate-400 hover:border-cyan-500 hover:text-cyan-600 dark:hover:text-cyan-400 shadow-xl\u0027\\n                  }`}\\n               \u003e\\n                 {isQuestioning ? \u003cMic className\u003d\\\"w-12 h-12 animate-pulse\\\" /\u003e : \u003cHand className\u003d\\\"w-12 h-12\\\" /\u003e}\\n                 \u003cspan className\u003d{`mt-2 text-[9px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] ${isQuestioning ? \u0027text-white\u0027 : \u0027text-slate-400\u0027}`}\u003e\\n                    {isQuestioning ? \u0027Speaking...\u0027 : \u0027Ask a Question\u0027}\\n                 \u003c/span\u003e\\n               \u003c/button\u003e\\n            \u003c/div\u003e\\n        \u003c/div\u003e\\n\\n        \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"absolute bottom-8 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 flex items-center gap-6 px-10 py-4 bg-white/70 dark:bg-slate-900/70 rounded-full backdrop-blur-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-white/5 shadow-2xl\\\"\u003e\\n             \u003cbutton \\n                onClick\u003d{() \u003d\u003e toggleLecture(false)}\\n                className\u003d{`py-3 px-8 rounded-xl font-bold text-xs flex items-center justify-center gap-3 transition-all ${\\n                    isLecturing \u0026\u0026 !isExamMode\\n                    ? \u0027bg-red-500 text-white\u0027 \\n                    : \u0027bg-cyan-600 text-white hover:bg-cyan-500\u0027\\n                }`}\\n            \u003e\\n                {isLecturing \u0026\u0026 !isExamMode ? \u003cSquare className\u003d\\\"w-3.5 h-3.5 fill-current\\\" /\u003e : \u003cPlay className\u003d\\\"w-3.5 h-3.5 fill-current\\\" /\u003e}\\n                {isLecturing \u0026\u0026 !isExamMode ? \u0027STOP SESSION\u0027 : \u0027START STUDY\u0027}\\n            \u003c/button\u003e\\n        \u003c/div\u003e\\n      \u003c/main\u003e\\n    \u003c/div\u003e\\n  );\\n};\\n\\nexport default App;\\n\"}]}]},\"createdTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767889643,\"nanos\":838000000},\"doneTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767889677,\"nanos\":500000000}},{\"id\":229,\"author\":\"user\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Intended area of study should consist of both secondary tertiary university colleges undergraduate postgraduate education, options let user type in what they would like to study \\nVocational Education should also include, \\nEducational orientation should be considered after sign up users by country , vocational training should also include \\nThis should let Gemini to know how to handle its student and how to set it up\",\"files\":[],\"fileUploads\":[],\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767890057,\"nanos\":948000000}},{\"id\":230,\"author\":\"model\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"text\":\"**Initiating Future Simulation**\\n\\nI\u0027m starting to build out a \\\"future of learning\\\" simulation. First, I\u0027m focusing on the introductory sequence; I plan to integrate a \\\"Welcome to the future of learning\\\" voice message using Gemini TTS. After that, I will design a new \\\"Auth Screen\\\" that presents \\\"Enrollment\\\" and \\\"Login\\\" options. This will be an initial step into creating the simulation, and I\u0027ll keep the user updated.\\n\\n\\n**Constructing Enrollment Forms**\\n\\nMy focus is now on the enrollment form. I\u0027m fleshing out the details, including fields for name, address, and past education - with options to specify educational goals and vocational interests via free text. The goal is to collect detailed user information to be utilized by Gemini for personalization. I am updating `types.ts` to include relevant fields to accommodate the data I\u0027m now collecting.\\n\\n\\n**Refining Enrollment \u0026 Syllabus**\\n\\nI\u0027ve been improving the enrollment form by adding country selection for educational orientation, using multi-step or detailed text for past education, implementing open text for specific study goals, and toggles or selections for vocational interests. I\u0027ve also refactored the syllabus to tailor content based on student profiles and updated the category names to match the user\u0027s request. Finally, I\u0027ve ensured the voice delivery is the primary trigger for navigation on the intro screen.\\n\\n\\n**Defining Core Functionality**\\n\\nI\u0027m now zeroing in on the app\u0027s core menu structure. I\u0027ve defined key sections like \\\"Class,\\\" \\\"Student Portal,\\\" \\\"Subjects,\\\" \\\"Learning Activities,\\\" and \\\"Alumni.\\\" I\u0027m also planning a futuristic \\\"Terminal\\\" aesthetic with sleek transitions and a dark mode. Code changes in `App.tsx`, `types.ts`, `components/Syllabus.tsx`, and `services/geminiService.ts` are underway to reflect these changes, including ensuring Gemini receives the complete student object for lecturer connection.\\n\\n\\n\",\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767890057,\"nanos\":948000000},\"doneTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767890077,\"nanos\":591000000}},{\"id\":231,\"author\":\"model\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"generationTable\",\"entries\":[{\"path\":\"types.ts\",\"generationType\":1,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"Extended StudentProfile to include detailed academic history, country for orientation, vocational interests, and specific study goals.\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"\\n/**\\n * @license\\n * SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0\\n*/\\nexport type AspectRatio \u003d \u002716:9\u0027 | \u00279:16\u0027 | \u00271:1\u0027;\\n\\nexport type ComplexityLevel \u003d \u0027Elementary\u0027 | \u0027High School\u0027 | \u0027College\u0027 | \u0027Expert\u0027;\\n\\nexport type SubscriptionTier \u003d \u0027Standard\u0027 | \u0027Scholar\u0027 | \u0027Grandmaster\u0027;\\n\\nexport type SubjectArea \u003d \\n  | \u0027STEM\u0027 \\n  | \u0027History\u0027 \\n  | \u0027Biology\u0027 \\n  | \u0027Physics\u0027 \\n  | \u0027Geography\u0027 \\n  | \u0027Literature\u0027 \\n  | \u0027Engineering\u0027 \\n  | \u0027Economics\u0027\\n  | \u0027Music Theory\u0027\\n  | \u0027Philosophy\u0027\\n  | \u0027Archeology\u0027\\n  | \u0027Linguistics\u0027\\n  | \u0027Astronomy\u0027\\n  | \u0027Vocational\u0027\\n  | \u0027General\u0027;\\n\\nexport interface StudentProfile {\\n  name: string;\\n  address: string;\\n  country: string;\\n  pastEducation: {\\n    level: string; // e.g. \\\"Postgraduate\\\"\\n    institution: string;\\n    details: string;\\n  };\\n  vocationalInterests: string[];\\n  studyGoals: string; // What exactly they want to study\\n  major: SubjectArea;\\n  level: ComplexityLevel;\\n  tier: SubscriptionTier;\\n  enrolledDate: number;\\n  studyHoursGoal: number;\\n  currentStudyHours: number;\\n}\\n\\nexport interface CourseTopic {\\n  id: string;\\n  title: string;\\n  duration: string;\\n  isCompleted: boolean;\\n  subject: SubjectArea;\\n  isLocked?: boolean;\\n}\\n\\nexport interface GeneratedImage {\\n  id: string;\\n  data: string;\\n  prompt: string;\\n  timestamp: number;\\n  level?: ComplexityLevel;\\n  style?: VisualStyle;\\n  language?: Language;\\n  subject?: SubjectArea;\\n}\\n\\nexport type VisualStyle \u003d \u0027Default\u0027 | \u0027Minimalist\u0027 | \u0027Realistic\u0027 | \u0027Cartoon\u0027 | \u0027Vintage\u0027 | \u0027Futuristic\u0027 | \u00273D Render\u0027 | \u0027Sketch\u0027;\\nexport type Language \u003d \u0027English\u0027 | \u0027Spanish\u0027 | \u0027French\u0027 | \u0027German\u0027 | \u0027Mandarin\u0027 | \u0027Japanese\u0027 | \u0027Hindi\u0027 | \u0027Arabic\u0027 | \u0027Portuguese\u0027 | \u0027Russian\u0027;\\n\\nexport interface SearchResultItem {\\n  title: string;\\n  url: string;\\n}\\n\\nexport interface ResearchResult {\\n  imagePrompt: string;\\n  facts: string[];\\n  searchResults: SearchResultItem[];\\n}\\n\\ndeclare global {\\n  interface AIStudio {\\n    hasSelectedApiKey: () \u003d\u003e Promise\u003cboolean\u003e;\\n    openSelectKey: () \u003d\u003e Promise\u003cvoid\u003e;\\n  }\\n  interface Window {\\n    SpeechRecognition: any;\\n    webkitSpeechRecognition: any;\\n  }\\n}\\n\"}]},{\"path\":\"App.tsx\",\"generationType\":1,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"Updated the enrollment flow and dashboard to satisfy the \\\"Menu\\\" button requirement and detailed student information gathering.\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"\\n/**\\n * @license\\n * SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0\\n*/\\nimport React, { useState, useEffect, useRef } from \u0027react\u0027;\\nimport { GeneratedImage, ComplexityLevel, VisualStyle, Language, SubjectArea, CourseTopic, StudentProfile, SubscriptionTier } from \u0027./types\u0027;\\nimport { connectLecturer, generateInfographicImage } from \u0027./services/geminiService\u0027;\\nimport { decode, decodeAudioData, createBlob } from \u0027./services/audioService\u0027;\\nimport Infographic from \u0027./components/Infographic\u0027;\\nimport Syllabus from \u0027./components/Syllabus\u0027;\\nimport IntroScreen from \u0027./components/IntroScreen\u0027;\\nimport { Sun, Moon, Mic, Hand, Volume2, Menu, X, Award, CheckCircle2, Sparkles, ShieldCheck, GraduationCap, ArrowLeft, UserCircle, MapPin, Book, Heart, Play, Square, Globe, Briefcase } from \u0027lucide-react\u0027;\\n\\ntype ViewState \u003d \u0027intro\u0027 | \u0027auth\u0027 | \u0027enroll\u0027 | \u0027dashboard\u0027 | \u0027class\u0027;\\n\\nconst App: React.FC \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\\n  const [view, setView] \u003d useState\u003cViewState\u003e(\u0027intro\u0027);\\n  const [currentTopic, setCurrentTopic] \u003d useState\u003cstring\u003e(\u0027Introduction to Your Custom Path\u0027);\\n  const [complexityLevel, setComplexityLevel] \u003d useState\u003cComplexityLevel\u003e(\u0027College\u0027);\\n  const [visualStyle, setVisualStyle] \u003d useState\u003cVisualStyle\u003e(\u0027Futuristic\u0027);\\n  \\n  const [isLecturing, setIsLecturing] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [isQuestioning, setIsQuestioning] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [currentSlide, setCurrentSlide] \u003d useState\u003cGeneratedImage | null\u003e(null);\\n  const [isDarkMode, setIsDarkMode] \u003d useState(true);\\n  const [isSidebarOpen, setIsSidebarOpen] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [isExamMode, setIsExamMode] \u003d useState(false);\\n\\n  const [student, setStudent] \u003d useState\u003cStudentProfile | null\u003e(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    const saved \u003d localStorage.getItem(\u0027student_profile\u0027);\\n    return saved ? JSON.parse(saved) : null;\\n  });\\n\\n  // Detailed Enrollment form state\\n  const [enrollForm, setEnrollForm] \u003d useState({\\n    name: \u0027\u0027,\\n    address: \u0027\u0027,\\n    country: \u0027\u0027,\\n    pastLevel: \u0027University\u0027,\\n    pastInstitution: \u0027\u0027,\\n    pastDetails: \u0027\u0027,\\n    vocationalInterests: [] as string[],\\n    studyGoals: \u0027\u0027,\\n    major: \u0027General\u0027 as SubjectArea,\\n    tier: \u0027Standard\u0027 as SubscriptionTier\\n  });\\n\\n  const audioContextRef \u003d useRef\u003cAudioContext | null\u003e(null);\\n  const outputAudioContextRef \u003d useRef\u003cAudioContext | null\u003e(null);\\n  const sessionRef \u003d useRef\u003cany\u003e(null);\\n  const nextStartTimeRef \u003d useRef(0);\\n  const sourcesRef \u003d useRef\u003cSet\u003cAudioBufferSourceNode\u003e\u003e(new Set());\\n\\n  const [topics, setTopics] \u003d useState\u003cCourseTopic[]\u003e([\\n    { id: \u00271\u0027, title: \u0027Personalized Academic Orientation\u0027, duration: \u00271.0 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: \u0027General\u0027 },\\n    { id: \u00272\u0027, title: \u0027Specialized Discipline Overview\u0027, duration: \u00272.0 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: \u0027STEM\u0027, isLocked: true },\\n  ]);\\n\\n  useEffect(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (isDarkMode) document.documentElement.classList.add(\u0027dark\u0027);\\n    else document.documentElement.classList.remove(\u0027dark\u0027);\\n  }, [isDarkMode]);\\n\\n  useEffect(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (student) {\\n      localStorage.setItem(\u0027student_profile\u0027, JSON.stringify(student));\\n      // Dynamically generate topics or set locks based on student data\\n      setTopics([\\n        { id: \u00271\u0027, title: `Orientation: ${student.major} in ${student.country}`, duration: \u00271.0 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: student.major },\\n        { id: \u00272\u0027, title: `Advanced ${student.studyGoals.substring(0, 20)}...`, duration: \u00273.5 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: student.major, isLocked: student.tier \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027Standard\u0027 },\\n      ]);\\n    }\\n  }, [student]);\\n\\n  const toggleLecture \u003d async (exam: boolean \u003d false) \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (isLecturing) {\\n      sessionRef.current?.close?.();\\n      setIsLecturing(false);\\n      return;\\n    }\\n\\n    if (!(await window.aistudio.hasSelectedApiKey())) {\\n      await window.aistudio.openSelectKey();\\n    }\\n\\n    try {\\n      const audioCtx \u003d new (window.AudioContext || (window as any).webkitAudioContext)({ sampleRate: 16000 });\\n      const outputCtx \u003d new (window.AudioContext || (window as any).webkitAudioContext)({ sampleRate: 24000 });\\n      audioContextRef.current \u003d audioCtx;\\n      outputAudioContextRef.current \u003d outputCtx;\\n\\n      const stream \u003d await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ audio: true });\\n      const source \u003d audioCtx.createMediaStreamSource(stream);\\n      const scriptProcessor \u003d audioCtx.createScriptProcessor(4096, 1, 1);\\n\\n      const sessionPromise \u003d connectLecturer({\\n        onopen: () \u003d\u003e {\\n          source.connect(scriptProcessor);\\n          scriptProcessor.connect(audioCtx.destination);\\n        },\\n        onmessage: async (message: any) \u003d\u003e {\\n          const base64Audio \u003d message.serverContent?.modelTurn?.parts[0]?.inlineData?.data;\\n          if (base64Audio \u0026\u0026 outputAudioContextRef.current) {\\n            const ctx \u003d outputAudioContextRef.current;\\n            nextStartTimeRef.current \u003d Math.max(nextStartTimeRef.current, ctx.currentTime);\\n            const audioBuffer \u003d await decodeAudioData(decode(base64Audio), ctx, 24000, 1);\\n            const sourceNode \u003d ctx.createBufferSource();\\n            sourceNode.buffer \u003d audioBuffer;\\n            sourceNode.connect(ctx.destination);\\n            sourceNode.start(nextStartTimeRef.current);\\n            nextStartTimeRef.current +\u003d audioBuffer.duration;\\n            sourcesRef.current.add(sourceNode);\\n          }\\n          if (message.toolCall) {\\n            for (const fc of message.toolCall.functionCalls) {\\n              if (fc.name \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027render_visual\u0027) {\\n                const data \u003d await generateInfographicImage(fc.args.description);\\n                setCurrentSlide({ id: Date.now().toString(), data, prompt: fc.args.description, timestamp: Date.now() });\\n                sessionPromise.then(s \u003d\u003e s.sendToolResponse({ functionResponses: { id: fc.id, name: fc.name, response: { result: \\\"Visual aid updated.\\\" } } }));\\n              }\\n            }\\n          }\\n        },\\n        onerror: (e: any) \u003d\u003e console.error(e),\\n        onclose: () \u003d\u003e setIsLecturing(false)\\n      }, student!, currentTopic);\\n\\n      scriptProcessor.onaudioprocess \u003d (e) \u003d\u003e {\\n        const inputData \u003d e.inputBuffer.getChannelData(0);\\n        const pcmBlob \u003d createBlob(inputData);\\n        sessionPromise.then(session \u003d\u003e session.sendRealtimeInput({ media: pcmBlob }));\\n      };\\n\\n      sessionRef.current \u003d await sessionPromise;\\n      setIsLecturing(true);\\n      setIsSidebarOpen(false);\\n    } catch (e) { console.error(e); }\\n  };\\n\\n  const handleEnrollSubmit \u003d (e: React.FormEvent) \u003d\u003e {\\n    e.preventDefault();\\n    const newStudent: StudentProfile \u003d {\\n      name: enrollForm.name,\\n      address: enrollForm.address,\\n      country: enrollForm.country,\\n      pastEducation: {\\n        level: enrollForm.pastLevel,\\n        institution: enrollForm.pastInstitution,\\n        details: enrollForm.pastDetails\\n      },\\n      vocationalInterests: enrollForm.vocationalInterests,\\n      studyGoals: enrollForm.studyGoals,\\n      major: enrollForm.major,\\n      level: \u0027College\u0027,\\n      tier: enrollForm.tier,\\n      enrolledDate: Date.now(),\\n      studyHoursGoal: 5,\\n      currentStudyHours: 0\\n    };\\n    setStudent(newStudent);\\n    setView(\u0027dashboard\u0027);\\n  };\\n\\n  const handleLogout \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\\n    setStudent(null);\\n    localStorage.removeItem(\u0027student_profile\u0027);\\n    setView(\u0027intro\u0027);\\n  };\\n\\n  if (view \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027intro\u0027) return \u003cIntroScreen onComplete\u003d{() \u003d\u003e setView(\u0027auth\u0027)} studentName\u003d{student?.name} /\u003e;\\n\\n  if (view \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027auth\u0027) return (\\n    \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center bg-slate-950 p-6 text-center\\\"\u003e\\n      \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_center,_var(--tw-gradient-stops))] from-cyan-900/20 via-slate-950 to-black pointer-events-none\\\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\\n      \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"relative z-10 max-w-md w-full space-y-8 animate-in fade-in duration-1000\\\"\u003e\\n         \u003cGraduationCap className\u003d\\\"w-20 h-20 text-cyan-500 mx-auto\\\" /\u003e\\n         \u003ch2 className\u003d\\\"text-4xl font-display font-bold text-white tracking-tighter\\\"\u003eVision University Portal\u003c/h2\u003e\\n         \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"flex flex-col gap-4 pt-8\\\"\u003e\\n            \u003cbutton onClick\u003d{() \u003d\u003e setView(\u0027enroll\u0027)} className\u003d\\\"w-full py-5 bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-2xl font-bold shadow-2xl hover:bg-cyan-500 transition-all\\\"\u003eNEW ENROLLMENT\u003c/button\u003e\\n            \u003cbutton onClick\u003d{() \u003d\u003e student ? setView(\u0027dashboard\u0027) : setView(\u0027enroll\u0027)} className\u003d\\\"w-full py-5 bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-2xl font-bold border border-white/10 hover:bg-slate-800 transition-all\\\"\u003eSTUDENT LOGIN\u003c/button\u003e\\n         \u003c/div\u003e\\n      \u003c/div\u003e\\n    \u003c/div\u003e\\n  );\\n\\n  if (view \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027enroll\u0027) return (\\n    \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"min-h-screen bg-slate-950 p-6 overflow-y-auto custom-scrollbar\\\"\u003e\\n      \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"max-w-2xl mx-auto w-full py-12 space-y-12 animate-in slide-in-from-bottom-8 duration-700\\\"\u003e\\n         \u003cbutton onClick\u003d{() \u003d\u003e setView(\u0027auth\u0027)} className\u003d\\\"text-slate-500 hover:text-white flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-bold\\\"\u003e\u003cArrowLeft className\u003d\\\"w-4 h-4\\\" /\u003e BACK\u003c/button\u003e\\n         \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"space-y-2\\\"\u003e\\n            \u003ch2 className\u003d\\\"text-3xl font-display font-bold text-white\\\"\u003eEnrollment Registry\u003c/h2\u003e\\n            \u003cp className\u003d\\\"text-slate-400\\\"\u003eConfigure your academi