termine if I should refine it, or if there was a misunderstanding. I\u0027m focusing on clarifying if the existing selector needs modification, or if the request concerns its specific implementation.\\n\\n\\n**Refining the Style Options**\\n\\nI\u0027m now considering the best approach for the \\\"Visual Style\\\" selector in `Infographic.tsx`. It turns out that the selector already exists, but the user\u0027s list, \\\"Minimalist\\\", \\\"Realistic\\\", \\\"Cartoon\\\", and \\\"Futuristic,\\\" differs from the current options. My main focus is on making the existing component more user-friendly, and to ensure that it matches the user\u0027s specific request. It now seems prudent to update the `styles` array to reflect the exact options mentioned.\\n\\n\\n**Updating the Visual Selector**\\n\\nI\u0027m now revising the UI. The \\\"Visual Style\\\" selector will be replaced with icon-buttons or a segmented control for a more engaging UX. This update to `Infographic.tsx` limits the styles to \u0027Minimalist\u0027, \u0027Realistic\u0027, \u0027Cartoon\u0027, and \u0027Futuristic\u0027. I envision a horizontal, scrollable list of styled choice chips, with a cyan border and glow for the active state, each chip containing an icon.\\n\\n\\n**Adjusting Style Display**\\n\\nI\u0027m now revising my approach. I\u0027ve decided to refine the visual selector to only present the requested styles, \u0027Minimalist\u0027, \u0027Realistic\u0027, \u0027Cartoon\u0027, and \u0027Futuristic.\u0027 While the `VisualStyle` type in `types.ts` is wider, I\u0027ll filter the display options in `Infographic.tsx` for clarity. I\u0027m moving forward with clickable chips for a modern look, but need to check on tooltips and labels for each style for a smoother UX.\\n\\n\\n\",\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767891885,\"nanos\":750000000},\"doneTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767891894,\"nanos\":860000000}},{\"id\":249,\"author\":\"model\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"generationTable\",\"entries\":[{\"path\":\"components/Infographic.tsx\",\"generationType\":1,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"Updated the visual style selector from a standard dropdown to an interactive set of choice chips to provide a more intuitive and visually appealing experience, limiting options to Minimalist, Realistic, Cartoon, and Futuristic as requested.\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"\\n/**\\n * @license\\n * SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0\\n*/\\nimport React, { useState, useEffect } from \u0027react\u0027;\\nimport { GeneratedImage, ComplexityLevel, VisualStyle } from \u0027../types\u0027;\\nimport { Download, Edit3, Maximize2, X, ZoomIn, ZoomOut, RefreshCcw, Layers, Palette, Save, Check } from \u0027lucide-react\u0027;\\n\\ninterface InfographicProps {\\n  image: GeneratedImage;\\n  onEdit: (prompt: string) \u003d\u003e void;\\n  onRegenerate: (level: ComplexityLevel, style: VisualStyle) \u003d\u003e void;\\n  isEditing: boolean;\\n}\\n\\nconst Infographic: React.FC\u003cInfographicProps\u003e \u003d ({ image, onEdit, onRegenerate, isEditing }) \u003d\u003e {\\n  const [isFullscreen, setIsFullscreen] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [zoomLevel, setZoomLevel] \u003d useState(1);\\n  const [isEditMode, setIsEditMode] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [modifiedPrompt, setModifiedPrompt] \u003d useState(image.prompt);\\n  \\n  // Local state for regeneration selection\\n  const [selectedLevel, setSelectedLevel] \u003d useState\u003cComplexityLevel\u003e(image.level || \u0027College\u0027);\\n  const [selectedStyle, setSelectedStyle] \u003d useState\u003cVisualStyle\u003e(image.style || \u0027Futuristic\u0027);\\n\\n  useEffect(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    setModifiedPrompt(image.prompt);\\n  }, [image.prompt]);\\n\\n  const handleApplyModifiedPrompt \u003d (e: React.FormEvent) \u003d\u003e {\\n    e.preventDefault();\\n    if (!modifiedPrompt.trim()) return;\\n    onEdit(modifiedPrompt);\\n    setIsEditMode(false);\\n  };\\n\\n  const handleRegenerateClick