perience.\\n\\n\\n**Refactoring Parameter Handling**\\n\\nI\u0027m now revising my strategy. I\u0027ll modify `generateInfographicImage` to accept `level` and `style`, while evaluating how to improve the overall prompt structure. I see that `Infographic.tsx` already passes the required values via `onRegenerate`. I will now update `handleRegenerate` in `App.tsx` to ensure that it passes these parameters correctly through to the service. I am now considering how to best consolidate and refine the prompt construction within `geminiService.ts` for improved consistency and flexibility, based on the `complexityLevel` and `visualStyle` parameters.\\n\\n\\n**Enhancing Parameter Usage**\\n\\nI\u0027m now integrating the `level` and `style` parameters more directly within `geminiService.ts`. I will ensure the updated `generateInfographicImage` function signature accepts and uses these parameters to produce a more refined prompt. I\u0027m focusing on crafting a better prompt by leveraging the provided parameters. I\u0027ll also double-check that `App.tsx` and `Infographic.tsx` are using the new signature, to guarantee complete integration and proper behavior.\\n\\n\\n**Refining Prompt Construction**\\n\\nI\u0027m now focused on revising the prompt construction within `geminiService.ts`. I will modify `generateInfographicImage` to accept `selectedLevel` and `selectedStyle` parameters. I\u0027ll make sure it uses these parameters directly to produce more descriptive prompts. I\u0027m going to ensure the \u0027Regenerate\u0027 flow in `Infographic.tsx` picks up the state correctly. I will also check the types to ensure the visual styles shown in the UI are represented properly. I see that the `handleRegenerate` function in `App.tsx` is updating the state as expected.\\n\\n\\n**Adapting API Integration**\\n\\nI\u0027m now integrating the updated API for `generateInfographicImage` and have adapted `App.tsx` accordingly, but I\u0027m having a new thought. I realized the existing `handleEditPrompt` function should not automatically append level/style to the user\u0027s custom prompt. I need to make sure the level and style parameters are incorporated only when the user *doesn\u0027t* provide a custom prompt, to allow the functionality to be more robust. I\u0027m focusing on preserving the user\u0027s intent. I will determine how best to structure the prompt generation logic to allow for this.\\n\\n\\n**Optimizing Parameter Logic**\\n\\nI\u0027m now back to the parameter logic, specifically in `App.tsx` and `services/geminiService.ts`. I\u0027m evaluating changing `generateInfographicImage` to accept *either* a raw prompt string, *or* structured data including `topic`, `level`, `style`, and `student`. This looks like the simplest change, since the calling functions now handle all possible values. I will ensure that this change covers the `handleEditPrompt` and `handleRegenerate` cases in `App.tsx`, and also the `toggleLecture` case. I\u0027ll make sure the `generateInfographicImage` takes care of the cases of manually edited prompts versus automatic generation, to ensure the right prompt is passed.\\n\\n\\n**Defining Parameter Structure**\\n\\nI\u0027ve decided on the update for `generateInfographicImage` in `services/geminiService.ts`. I will update the function to accept an options object that can contain either a `prompt` string *or* structured data, which includes the `topic`, `level`, `style`, and `student` values. This change looks like the best approach to ensure that the function can take both edited raw prompts and structured data. Now I\u0027ll refactor `App.tsx` and ensure all paths can use the new signature.\\n\\n\\n**Updating Function Parameters**\\n\\nI\u0027m now focused on updating the function parameters for `generateInfographicImage` in `geminiService.ts`. I will update the `App.tsx` file by modifying `handleRegenerate` to pass structured data to the function instead of manually generating a prompt string. I\u0027ll also modify `handleEditPrompt` and the tool call to use the updated function signature. I\u0027ll make sure the `Regenerate` function in `Infographic.tsx` works by validating the existing code. I\u0027ll prioritize clean code.\\n\\n\\n**Refining Prompt Integration**\\n\\nI\u0027m now integrating the `level` and `style` parameters into the prompt generation process within `generateInfographicImage`. The goal is to craft a more nuanced prompt by using these parameters to improve the results. I\u0027m focusing on how `App.tsx` and the other components need to update the model to use the new parameters, while also making sure that the edited prompt functionality is maintained. I\u0027m currently working to ensure that the prompt reflects the selections.\\n\\n\\n\",\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767892126,\"nanos\":115000000},\"doneTimestamp\":{\"seconds\":1767892150,\"nanos\":35000000}},{\"id\":261,\"author\":\"model\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"generationTable\",\"entries\":[{\"path\":\"services/geminiService.ts\",\"generationType\":1,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"Updated generateInfographicImage to accept a structured options object, allowing the application to pass explicit complexity and style parameters for more controlled and descriptive prompt generation.\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"\\n/**\\n * @license\\n * SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0\\n*/\\nimport { GoogleGenAI, FunctionDeclaration, Modality, Type } from \\\"@google/genai\\\";\\nimport { ComplexityLevel, VisualStyle, ResearchResult, SearchResultItem, Language, SubjectArea, StudentProfile } from \\\"../types\\\";\\n\\nconst getAi \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\\n  return new GoogleGenAI({ apiKey: process.env.API_KEY });\\n};\\n\\nconst TEXT_MODEL \u003d \u0027gemini-3-pro-preview\u0027;\\nconst IMAGE_MODEL \u003d \u0027gemini-3-pro-image-preview\u0027;\\n\\nexport const generateWelcomeAudio \u003d async (text: string) \u003d\u003e {\\n  const ai \u003d getAi();\\n  const response \u003d await ai.models.generateContent({\\n    model: \\\"gemini-2.5-flash-preview-tts\\\",\\n    contents: [{ parts: [{ text }] }],\\n    config: {\\n      responseModalities: [Modality.AUDIO],\\n      speechConfig: {\\n        voiceConfig: {\\n          prebuiltVoiceConfig: { voiceName: \u0027Kore\u0027 },\\n        },\\n      },\\n    },\\n  });\\n  return response.candidates?.[0]?.content?.parts?.[0]?.inlineData?.data;\\n};\\n\\nexport const connectLecturer \u003d (\\n  callbacks: any,\\n  student: StudentProfile,\\n  topic: string\\n) \u003d\u003e {\\n  const ai \u003d getAi();\\n  \\n  const renderVisualTool: FunctionDeclaration \u003d {\\n    name: \u0027render_visual\u0027,\\n    parameters: {\\n      type: Type.OBJECT,\\n      description: \u0027Generate and render a detailed educational visual or infographic.\u0027,\\n      properties: {\\n        description: { type: Type.STRING, description: \u0027Visual description.\u0027 }\\n      },\\n      required: [\u0027description\u0027]\\n    }\\n  };\\n\\n  const instruction \u003d `You are Professor Alpha, a world-class lecturer at the Vision University. \\n       Explain \\\"${topic}\\\" to ${student.name}, currently located in ${student.country}.\\n       \\n       STUDENT CONTEXT:\\n       - Past Education: ${student.pastEducation.level} at ${student.pastEducation.institution}. \\n       - Background Details: ${student.pastEducation.details}.\\n       - Specific Study Goals: \\\"${student.studyGoals}\\\".\\n       - Vocational Interests: ${student.vocationalInterests.join(\u0027, \u0027)}.\\n       - Educational Orientation: Based on ${student.country}\u0027s academic standards and regional context.\\n       \\n       BEHAVIOR:\\n       - Tailor analogies to their past experience in ${student.pastEducation.level}.\\n       - Integrate vocational interests like ${student.vocationalInterests[0] || \u0027industry applications\u0027} where relevant.\\n       - Focus strictly on ${student.studyGoals} during the lecture.\\n       - Use \u0027render_visual\u0027 for infographics.\\n       - Tone: Warm, futuristic, encouraging.`;\\n\\n  return ai.live.connect({\\n    model: \u0027gemini-2.5-flash-native-audio-preview-12-2025\u0027,\\n    callbacks,\\n    config: {\\n      responseModalities: [Modality.AUDIO],\\n      systemInstruction: instruction,\\n      tools: [{ functionDeclarations: [renderVisualTool] }],\\n      speechConfig: {\\n        voiceConfig: { prebuiltVoiceConfig: { voiceName: \u0027Charon\u0027 } }\\n      }\\n    }\\n  });\\n};\\n\\ninterface VisualOptions {\\n  prompt?: string;\\n  topic?: string;\\n  level?: ComplexityLevel;\\n  style?: VisualStyle;\\n  student?: StudentProfile;\\n}\\n\\nexport const generateInfographicImage \u003d async (options: VisualOptions): Promise\u003cstring\u003e \u003d\u003e {\\n  let finalPrompt \u003d \u0027\u0027;\\n\\n  if (options.prompt) {\\n    finalPrompt \u003d options.prompt;\\n  } else {\\n    const { topic, level, style, student } \u003d options;\\n    finalPrompt \u003d `Create a high-quality educational infographic/visual about: ${topic}.\\n      Visual Style: ${style || \u0027Futuristic\u0027}\\n      Academic Complexity: ${level || \u0027College\u0027}\\n      Target Audience: A student named ${student?.name || \u0027Academic\u0027} with background in ${student?.pastEducation.level || \u0027Higher Education\u0027}.\\n      Context: Focus on ${student?.studyGoals || \u0027general education\u0027} and incorporate ${student?.vocationalInterests?.[0] || \u0027industry\u0027} perspectives.\\n      The visual should be clear, detailed, and use a consistent color palette matching the requested style.`;\\n  }\\n\\n  const response \u003d await getAi().models.generateContent({\\n    model: IMAGE_MODEL,\\n    contents: { parts: [{ text: finalPrompt }] },\\n    config: { imageConfig: { aspectRatio: \\\"16:9\\\", imageSize: \\\"1K\\\" } }\\n  });\\n\\n  const parts \u003d response.candidates?.[0]?.content?.parts || [];\\n  for (const part of parts) {\\n    if (part.inlineData?.data) return `data:image/png;base64,${part.inlineData.data}`;\\n  }\\n  throw new Error(\\\"Visual generation failed.\\\");\\n};\\n\"}]},{\"path\":\"App.tsx\",\"generationType\":1,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"Updated App.tsx to use the new structured signature for generateInfographicImage, passing explicit level and style parameters during regeneration to ensure the visual output is correctly tailored.\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"\\n/**\\n * @license\\n * SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0\\n*/\\nimport React, { useState, useEffect, useRef } from \u0027react\u0027;\\nimport { GeneratedImage, ComplexityLevel, VisualStyle, Language, SubjectArea, CourseTopic, StudentProfile, SubscriptionTier } from \u0027./types\u0027;\\nimport { connectLecturer, generateInfographicImage } from \u0027./services/geminiService\u0027;\\nimport { decode, decodePCM16, createBlob } from \u0027./services/audioService\u0027;\\nimport Infographic from \u0027./components/Infographic\u0027;\\nimport Syllabus from \u0027./components/Syllabus\u0027;\\nimport IntroScreen from \u0027./components/IntroScreen\u0027;\\nimport { Sun, Moon, Mic, Hand, Volume2, Menu, X, Award, CheckCircle2, Sparkles, ShieldCheck, GraduationCap, ArrowLeft, UserCircle, MapPin, Book, Heart, Play, Square, Globe, Briefcase } from \u0027lucide-react\u0027;\\n\\ntype ViewState \u003d \u0027intro\u0027 | \u0027auth\u0027 | \u0027enroll\u0027 | \u0027dashboard\u0027 | \u0027class\u0027;\\n\\nconst App: React.FC \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\\n  const [view, setView] \u003d useState\u003cViewState\u003e(\u0027intro\u0027);\\n  const [currentTopic, setCurrentTopic] \u003d useState\u003cstring\u003e(\u0027Introduction to Your Custom Path\u0027);\\n  const [complexityLevel, setComplexityLevel] \u003d useState\u003cComplexityLevel\u003e(\u0027College\u0027);\\n  const [visualStyle, setVisualStyle] \u003d useState\u003cVisualStyle\u003e(\u0027Futuristic\u0027);\\n  \\n  const [isLecturing, setIsLecturing] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [isQuestioning, setIsQuestioning] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [currentSlide, setCurrentSlide] \u003d useState\u003cGeneratedImage | null\u003e(null);\\n  const [isDarkMode, setIsDarkMode] \u003d useState(true);\\n  const [isSidebarOpen, setIsSidebarOpen] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [isExamMode, setIsExamMode] \u003d useState(false);\\n  const [isGeneratingVisual, setIsGeneratingVisual] \u003d useState(false);\\n\\n  const [student, setStudent] \u003d useState\u003cStudentProfile | null\u003e(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    const saved \u003d localStorage.getItem(\u0027student_profile\u0027);\\n    return saved ? JSON.parse(saved) : null;\\n  });\\n\\n  // Detailed Enrollment form state\\n  const [enrollForm, setEnrollForm] \u003d useState({\\n    name: \u0027\u0027,\\n    address: \u0027\u0027,\\n    country: \u0027\u0027,\\n    pastLevel: \u0027University\u0027,\\n    pastInstitution: \u0027\u0027,\\n    pastDetails: \u0027\u0027,\\n    vocationalInterests: [] as string[],\\n    studyGoals: \u0027\u0027,\\n    major: \u0027General\u0027 as SubjectArea,\\n    tier: \u0027Standard\u0027 as SubscriptionTier\\n  });\\n\\n  const audioContextRef \u003d useRef\u003cAudioContext | null\u003e(null);\\n  const outputAudioContextRef \u003d useRef\u003cAudioContext | null\u003e(null);\\n  const sessionRef \u003d useRef\u003cany\u003e(null);\\n  const nextStartTimeRef \u003d useRef(0);\\n  const sourcesRef \u003d useRef\u003cSet\u003cAudioBufferSourceNode\u003e\u003e(new Set());\\n\\n  const [topics, setTopics] \u003d useState\u003cCourseTopic[]\u003e([\\n    { id: \u00271\u0027, title: \u0027Personalized Academic Orientation\u0027, duration: \u00271.0 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: \u0027General\u0027 },\\n    { id: \u00272\u0027, title: \u0027Specialized Discipline Overview\u0027, duration: \u00272.0 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: \u0027STEM\u0027, isLocked: true },\\n  ]);\\n\\n  useEffect(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (isDarkMode) document.documentElement.classList.add(\u0027dark\u0027);\\n    else document.documentElement.classList.remove(\u0027dark\u0027);\\n  }, [isDarkMode]);\\n\\n  useEffect(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (student) {\\n      localStorage.setItem(\u0027student_profile\u0027, JSON.stringify(student));\\n      setTopics([\\n        { id: \u00271\u0027, title: `Orientation: ${student.major} in ${student.country}`, duration: \u00271.0 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: student.major },\\n        { id: \u00272\u0027, title: `Advanced Study: ${student.studyGoals.substring(0, 30)}...`, duration: \u00273.5 hrs\u0027, isCompleted: false, subject: student.major, isLocked: student.tier \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027Standard\u0027 },\\n      ]);\\n    }\\n  }, [student]);\\n\\n  const handleRegenerate \u003d async (level: ComplexityLevel, style: VisualStyle) \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (!(await window.aistudio.hasSelectedApiKey())) {\\n      await window.aistudio.openSelectKey();\\n    }\\n    setComplexityLevel(level);\\n    setVisualStyle(style);\\n    setIsGeneratingVisual(true);\\n    \\n    try {\\n      const data \u003d await generateInfographicImage({\\n        topic: currentTopic,\\n        level: level,\\n        style: style,\\n        student: student || undefined\\n      });\\n      setCurrentSlide({\\n        id: Date.now().toString(),\\n        data,\\n        prompt: `Educational visual about ${currentTopic}, ${style} style, ${level} complexity.`,\\n        timestamp: Date.now(),\\n        level: level,\\n        style: style\\n      });\\n    } catch (e: any) {\\n      if (e?.message?.includes(\\\"Requested entity was not found.\\\")) {\\n        await window.aistudio.openSelectKey();\\n      }\\n      console.error(\\\"Regeneration failed\\\", e);\\n    } finally {\\n      setIsGeneratingVisual(false);\\n    }\\n  };\\n\\n  const handleEditPrompt \u003d async (newPrompt: string) \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (!(await window.aistudio.hasSelectedApiKey())) {\\n        await window.aistudio.openSelectKey();\\n    }\\n    setIsGeneratingVisual(true);\\n    try {\\n      const data \u003d await generateInfographicImage({ prompt: newPrompt });\\n      setCurrentSlide({\\n        id: Date.now().toString(),\\n        data,\\n        prompt: newPrompt,\\n        timestamp: Date.now(),\\n        level: complexityLevel,\\n        style: visualStyle\\n      });\\n    } catch (e: any) {\\n      if (e?.message?.includes(\\\"Requested entity was not found.\\\")) {\\n        await window.aistudio.openSelectKey();\\n      }\\n      console.error(\\\"Edit prompt failed\\\", e);\\n    } finally {\\n      setIsGeneratingVisual(false);\\n    }\\n  };\\n\\n  const toggleLecture \u003d async (exam: boolean \u003d false) \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (isLecturing) {\\n      sessionRef.current?.close?.();\\n      setIsLecturing(false);\\n      return;\\n    }\\n\\n    if (!(await window.aistudio.hasSelectedApiKey())) {\\n      await window.aistudio.openSelectKey();\\n    }\\n\\n    try {\\n      const audioCtx \u003d new (window.AudioContext || (window as any).webkitAudioContext)({ sampleRate: 16000 });\\n      const outputCtx \u003d new (window.AudioContext || (window as any).webkitAudioContext)({ sampleRate: 24000 });\\n      audioContextRef.current \u003d audioCtx;\\n      outputAudioContextRef.current \u003d outputCtx;\\n\\n      const stream \u003d await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ audio: true });\\n      const source \u003d audioCtx.createMediaStreamSource(stream);\\n      const scriptProcessor \u003d audioCtx.createScriptProcessor(4096, 1, 1);\\n\\n      const sessionPromise \u003d connectLecturer({\\n        onopen: () \u003d\u003e {\\n          source.connect(scriptProcessor);\\n          scriptProcessor.connect(audioCtx.destination);\\n        },\\n        onmessage: async (message: any) \u003d\u003e {\\n          const base64Audio \u003d message.serverContent?.modelTurn?.parts[0]?.inlineData?.data;\\n          if (base64Audio \u0026\u0026 outputAudioContextRef.current) {\\n            const ctx \u003d outputAudioContextRef.current;\\n            nextStartTimeRef.current \u003d Math.max(nextStartTimeRef.current, ctx.currentTime);\\n            // Use custom PCM decoder\\n            const audioBuffer \u003d decodePCM16(decode(base64Audio), ctx, 24000, 1);\\n            const sourceNode \u003d ctx.createBufferSource();\\n            sourceNode.buffer \u003d audioBuffer;\\n            sourceNode.connect(ctx.destination);\\n            sourceNode.start(nextStartTimeRef.current);\\n            nextStartTimeRef.current +\u003d audioBuffer.duration;\\n            sourcesRef.current.add(sourceNode);\\n          }\\n          if (message.toolCall) {\\n            for (const fc of message.toolCall.functionCalls) {\\n              if (fc.name \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027render_visual\u0027) {\\n                const data \u003d await generateInfographicImage({ prompt: fc.args.description });\\n                setCurrentSlide({ id: Date.now().toString(), data, prompt: fc.args.description, timestamp: Date.now() });\\n                sessionPromise.then(s \u003d\u003e s.sendToolResponse({ functionResponses: { id: fc.id, name: fc.name, response: { result: \\\"Visual aid updated.\\\" } } }));\\n              }\\n            }\\n          }\\n        },\\n        onerror: (e: any) \u003d\u003e console.error(e),\\n        onclose: () \u003d\u003e setIsLecturing(false)\\n      }, student!, currentTopic);\\n\\n      scriptProcessor.onaudioprocess \u003d (e) \u003d\u003e {\\n        const inputData \u003d e.inputBuffer.getChannelData(0);\\n        const pcmBlob \u003d createBlob(inputData);\\n        sessionPromise.then(session \u003d\u003e session.sendRealtimeInput({ media: pcmBlob }));\\n      };\\n\\n      sessionRef.current \u003d await sessionPromise;\\n      setIsLecturing(true);\\n      setIsSidebarOpen(false);\\n    } catch (e) { console.error(e); }\\n  };\\n\\n  const handleEnrollSubmit \u003d (e: React.FormEvent) \u003d\u003e {\\n    e.preventDefault();\\n    const newStudent: StudentProfile \u003d {\\n      name: enrollForm.name,\\n      address: enrollForm.address,\\n      country: enrollForm.country,\\n      pastEducation: {\\n        level: enrollForm.pastLevel,\\n        institution: enrollForm.pastInstitution,\\n        details: enrollForm.pastDetails\\n      },\\n      vocationalInterests: enrollForm.vocationalInterests,\\n      studyGoals: enrollForm.studyGoals,\\n      major: enrollForm.major,\\n      level: \u0027College\u0027,\\n      tier: enrollForm.tier,\\n      enrolledDate: Date.now(),\\n      studyHoursGoal: 5,\\n      currentStudyHours: 0\\n    };\\n    setStudent(newStudent);\\n    setView(\u0027dashboard\u0027);\\n  };\\n\\n  const handleLogout \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\\n    setStudent(null);\\n    localStorage.removeItem(\u0027student_profile\u0027);\\n    setView(\u0027intro\u0027);\\n  };\\n\\n  if (view \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027intro\u0027) return \u003cIntroScreen onComplete\u003d{() \u003d\u003e setView(\u0027auth\u0027)} studentName\u003d{student?.name} /\u003e;\\n\\n  if (view \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027auth\u0027) return (\\n    \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center bg-slate-950 p-6 text-center\\\"\u003e\\n      \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_center,_var(--tw-gradient-stops))] from-cyan-900/20 via-slate-950 to-black pointer-events-none\\\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\\n      \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"relative z-10 max-w-md w-full space-y-8 animate-in fade-in duration-1000\\\"\u003e\\n         \u003cGraduationCap className\u003d\\\"w-20 h-20 text-cyan-500 mx-auto\\\" /\u003e\\n         \u003ch2 className\u003d\\\"text-4xl font-display font-bold text-white tracking-tighter\\\"\u003eVision University Portal\u003c/h2\u003e\\n         \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"flex flex-col gap-4 pt-8\\\"\u003e\\n            \u003cbutton 